Subcode.Label: Mine
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An excavation made in the earth for the purpose of extracting natural deposits. (See also AQ090)

Subcode.Label: Quarry_Wall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The wall facing of the excavation within a quarry/mine.

Subcode.Label: Quarry
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An excavation created by removal of stone by blasting or cutting.

Subcode.Label: Pit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An excavation where gravel, sand, or clay are removed for use elsewhere.

Subcode.Label: Rig_or_Superstructure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A vertical structure fitted for drilling or lifting operations.

Subcode.Label: Well
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A hole drilled or dug into the earth or sea bed for the extraction of liquids or gases. (See also BH170)

Subcode.Label: Wellhead
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The top of a well, as in oil, gas, or water well, that caps the well structure and which may be located on land or partially submerged offshore which nautical vessels can use for lashings.

Subcode.Label: Oil_or_Gas_Field
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where oil and/or gas is pumped or otherwise removed from the ground.

Subcode.Label: Gradation_Work
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Trestle covered with twigs over which brine trickles that is concentrated through increased evaporation.

Subcode.Label: Disposal_Site
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site for the collecting/depositing of refuse or discarded material. (See also AB010, AM010 and AM040)

Subcode.Label: Scrap_Yard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area or site engaged in the wrecking, dismantling, storage, or resale of discarded products. (See also AB000)

Subcode.Label: Incinerator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A permanent structure used for the disposal of waste products by burning.

Subcode.Label: Burner_Stack
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A permanent structure used for the disposal of waste products by burning.

Subcode.Label: Diffuser
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An artificial installation at or below water level, where liquids (e.g. cooling water, spillage) are spread out.

Subcode.Label: Waste_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Operational site with buildings and other facilities, where waste is processed through chemical, physical, biological or thermal procedures or a combination of those procedures. (See also AB000 and AB020)

Subcode.Label: Aeration_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A basin, usually artificial, in which air is mixed with partially treated wastewater.

Subcode.Label: Waste_Heap
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where heaped material (for example: waste or spoil) is deposited.

Subcode.Label: Treatment_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site used for changing or refining a particular material.

Subcode.Label: Blast_Furnace
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A heat chamber used for smelting iron ore.

Subcode.Label: Catalytic_Cracker
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A unit in which petroleum separation is carried out in the presence of a catalyst.

Subcode.Label: Settling_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site where solid matter is precipitated from a liquid by evaporating or settling.

Subcode.Label: Oil_or_Gas_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area involved in the production or distribution of oil or natural gas.

Subcode.Label: Works
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The structures, grounds, machinery etc. of a manufacturing establishment or structures in engineering such as docks, bridges.

Subcode.Label: Industrial_Furnace
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure used in material processing that employs heating to harden (for example: to fire brick or ceramic), pyrolyse (for example: convert coal to coke, or limestone to lime), burn (for example: to incinerate waste), or dry (for example: lumber).

Subcode.Label: Industrial_Park
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An industrial facility consisting of buildings and related structures that are tenanted by multiple manufacturing (for example: industrial equipment manufacture or materials processing) and/or service businesses (for example: auto repair or residential contractors) requiring significant equipment and/or materials, and sharing common access to adjacent transport facilities.

Subcode.Label: Sewage_Treatment_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An operational area with buildings and other facilities for the purification of wastewater.

Subcode.Label: Power_Plant_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation. (See also AD020)

Subcode.Label: Hydro-electric
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; a hydro-electric power plant.

Subcode.Label: Nuclear
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; a nuclear power plant.

Subcode.Label: Solar
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; a solar power plant.

Subcode.Label: Thermal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; a thermal power plant.

Subcode.Label: Wind
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; a wind/windfarm power plant.

Subcode.Label: Tidal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; a tidal power plant.

Subcode.Label: Internal_Comb
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; an Internal Combustion power plant.

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility including one or more buildings and equipment used for power generation; other types of power plant.

Subcode.Label: Solar_Panel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Units of solar cells for converting sunlight into electrical energy or heat. (See also AD010)

Subcode.Label: Solar_Farm
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An extensive collection of solar panels that are collocated and serve a common purpose (for example: the generation of electricity or the generation of heating steam and/or water).

Subcode.Label: Substation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility, along a power line route, in which electric current is transformed and/or distributed.

Subcode.Label: Nuclear_Reactor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An apparatus in which a nuclear chain reaction is initiated, sustained, and controlled. (See also AD010) This code is used to define a nuclear reactor which may be contained within a power plant.

Subcode.Label: Nuclear_Reactor_Containment
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building-like structure intended to create a barrier against the release of radioactivity generated during nuclear power operations.

Subcode.Label: Heating_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Operational site with buildings and other facilities for the generation of thermal energy for heating purposes.

Subcode.Label: Cooling_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility for the removal of thermal energy (for example: by generating and circulating chilled water) for cooling purposes.

Subcode.Label: Wind_Farm
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A collection of windmotors that are collocated and are organized as a single power generation unit.

Subcode.Label: Assembly_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building or group of buildings used for the purpose of combining manufactured parts to make a completed product.

Subcode.Label: Smokestack
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A vertical structure containing a passage or flue for discharging smoke and gases of combustion.

Subcode.Label: Conveyor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An apparatus for moving materials from place to place on a moving belt or series of rollers.

Subcode.Label: Bucket_Elevator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A machine, usually a series of buckets, for raising materials or liquids to a higher level.

Subcode.Label: Cooling_Tower
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tower used to cool liquids.

Subcode.Label: Crane
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A machine for lifting, shifting, and lowering objects or materials by means of a swinging boom or with the lifting apparatus supported on an overhead track.

Subcode.Label: Sheerleg
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Comprises two or three spars standing on end and lashed together, aloft. They serve as a derrick or tripod to lift heavy weights, step or lower masts, stacks, etc.

Subcode.Label: Dredger
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An excavating machine for removing earth or materials.

Subcode.Label: Engine_Cell
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure wherein engines are tested.

Subcode.Label: Flare_Pipe
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open-ended pipe at which waste gases are burned.

Subcode.Label: Hopper
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A top-loaded funnel-shaped structure for temporary holding of loose material which will be dispensed from its bottom.

Subcode.Label: Shopping_Complex
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A commercial facility tenanted by multiple retail stores (for example: household goods, clothing, or books), restaurants (for example: a food court), entertainment venues (for example: a movie theatre or electronic games arcade), and/or other businesses (for example: professional services), that is completely enclosed, climate controlled, has a common public arcade (for example: furnished with decorative plantings, benches, and/or fountains) and a common vehicle parking area (for example: a parking lot or parking garage).

Subcode.Label: Office_Park
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A commercial facility consisting of multiple office buildings tenanted by one or more non-retail businesses (for example: corporate management, consulting services, or research and development) and supportive businesses (for example: a restaurant serving mid-day meals or a post office) that share a common park-like setting consisting of landscaping (for example: lawns, ornamental plantings, or ponds), parking facilities, and common entrances from adjacent roads.

Subcode.Label: Billboard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large outdoor board for advertisements.

Subcode.Label: Bastion
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A defensive wall built to defend a fort or other defensive work and sometimes equipped with guns.

Subcode.Label: Trench
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A linear excavation dug for defensive purposes.

Subcode.Label: Hazard_Shelter
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure intended for short term occupancy to protect personnel from injury.

Subcode.Label: Fortification
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility constructed for the military defense of a site. (See also AM060)

Subcode.Label: Bunker
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An underground facility used by the military either for location of command/control centers or for troop encampment. (See also AL250)

Subcode.Label: Checkpoint
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An official place to register, declare or check goods and people.

Subcode.Label: Mobile_Home_Park
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site for the permanent parking of trailer(s) used as dwellings and designed without a permanent foundation. (See also AK060 and AQ140)

Subcode.Label: Camp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A place where tents or buildings serve as temporary residence for members of an organization.

Subcode.Label: Circular_Irrigation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An elevated irrigation system revolving around a central pivot point.

Subcode.Label: Siphon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Bent or curved tube so arranged that liquid flows up or down through it under the force of gravity.

Subcode.Label: Stockyard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An enclosed area in which livestock are temporarily kept.

Subcode.Label: Windmill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A wind-driven system of vanes attached to a tower like structure (excluding wind-generated power plants).

Subcode.Label: Windmotor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modern structure used for wind power.

Subcode.Label: Water_Mill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure that uses a water wheel or turbine to drive a mechanical process (for example: grinding grain into flour, cutting timber into lumber, or stripping bark from trees for use in tanning).

Subcode.Label: Farm
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tract of land, including buildings and structures, whose primary use is the production of food (for example: crops or livestock).

Subcode.Label: Ranch
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tract of land, including buildings and structures, whose primary use is the grazing of livestock on large, mostly unimproved, lands that are otherwise unsuitable for farming (for example: arid).

Subcode.Label: Stable
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building similar to a barn and adapted for the shelter and feeding of domestic animals, being divided into individual stalls.

Subcode.Label: Barn
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A roofed farm building designed for sheltering harvested crops (for example: hay), livestock (for example: cattle), and/or farm machinery (for example: tractors and plows).

Subcode.Label: Cattle_Dipping_Tank
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small artificial pond used for immersing cattle in chemically treated water for disease control.

Subcode.Label: Agricultural_Colony
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tract of land set aside for agricultural settlement.

Subcode.Label: Greenhouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building constructed primarily of transparent material (for example: glass or plastic), in which temperature and humidity can be controlled for the cultivation and/or protection of plants.

Subcode.Label: Water_Wheel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A wheel, one portion of which is immersed in water, that consists of vanes or cells and rotates on a supporting framework.

Subcode.Label: Grange
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A farm, especially a country house with out-buildings attached, that is closed to the street by a gate or by a vertical building with a gate in it.

Subcode.Label: Bandshell
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An outdoor band-stand in the form of a large concave shell with special acoustical properties.

Subcode.Label: Amst_Pk_Attract
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large structure located in an Amusement Park.

Subcode.Label: Amst_Pk
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A predominantly man-made facility equipped with recreational devices. (See also AK090 and AK120)

Subcode.Label: Athletic_Field
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open area where sporting events, exercises, or games occur.

Subcode.Label: Tennis_Court
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area or site used for the sport of tennis.

Subcode.Label: Tennis_Complex
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site and associated facilities used for the sport of tennis.

Subcode.Label: Campground
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A location for camping. (See also AI020 and AQ140)

Subcode.Label: Picnic_Site
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A parcel of land that has picnic tables for public use.

Subcode.Label: Drive-In_Theater
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A place where motion pictures are shown while viewers remain in their vehicles.

Subcode.Label: Theater_Screen
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large outdoor screen for showing motion pictures.

Subcode.Label: Fairground
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where permanent facilities exist to hold outdoor fairs, circuses or exhibitions. (See also AK091, AK030 and AK120)

Subcode.Label: Exhibition_Ground
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where permanent facilities exist to hold outdoor exhibitions. (Superseeded by AK090)

Subcode.Label: Golf_Course
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of land laid out for the game of golf.

Subcode.Label: Golf_Driving_Range
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A parcel or tract of land used for practicing golf shots.

Subcode.Label: Grandstand
Subcode.Concept_Definition: AA usually roofed structure for special viewing of events and having tiers of seats or standing room for spectators.

Subcode.Label: Park
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area used for recreational or ornamental purposes. (See also AK030, AK090 and AL170)

Subcode.Label: Lookout
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area, generally an elevated place, with facilities for observing the scenery.

Subcode.Label: Green_Space
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A maintained vegetated area, which may also contain pathways. Its primary intent is to improve the appearance of a Built-Up Area, and which is not a park. (See also AK120)

Subcode.Label: Bench
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A long hard seat for two or more persons.

Subcode.Label: Picnic_Table
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A table used for picnics.

Subcode.Label: Race_Track
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A course for racing.

Subcode.Label: Planter
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A container for growing or displaying plants, usually decorative and permanent.

Subcode.Label: Statue_Pedestal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An architectural support or base for a statue.

Subcode.Label: Ski_Jump
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A ramp used for ski jumping.

Subcode.Label: Ski_Track
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A course prepared for skiing.

Subcode.Label: Stadium
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An arena for holding and viewing events.

Subcode.Label: Scoreboard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large outdoor board for publicly displaying the score in an athletic event.

Subcode.Label: Amphitheatre
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small tract of level ground serving as a stage that is surrounded by rising slopes (either naturally occurring or artificially constructed) supporting tiered seating (for example: benches).

Subcode.Label: Sports_Stadium
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An athletic field partially or completely surrounded by a structure designed to allow spectators to stand or sit and view the event.

Subcode.Label: Arena
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building enclosing a large open area, often circular or oval-shaped, surrounded on most or all sides by tiered seating for spectators.

Subcode.Label: Swimming_Pool
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A constructed basin used for swimming outdoors.

Subcode.Label: Zoo
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area with a collection of live animals usually for public display.

Subcode.Label: Fishing
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure extending into the water used as a platform for recreational purposes, not intended as a berthing place for vessels.

Subcode.Label: Spa
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A resort town or area centered around mineral and/or hot springs that are believed to have restorative powers.

Subcode.Label: Open_Air_Bath
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility with a swimming pool and/or located on the bank of a water body that is used for bathing or swimming.

Subcode.Label: Animal_Sanctuary
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A natural area set aside for the preservation and protection of wildlife.

Subcode.Label: Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area that has been developed to perform a specific principal function, consisting of one or more vertical constructions (for example: structures or buildings), horizontal constructions (for example: pavements, roads, rail tracks, or bridges), and/or supporting utilities (for example: power lines, water supply, or sewerage), plus the underlying land.

Subcode.Label: Installation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A grouping of facilities, located in the same vicinity, which support particular functions (for example: military operations).

Subcode.Label: Arch_Site
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site or location where remains of ancient civilizations or human activity have been discovered. (See also AL200)

Subcode.Label: Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A free-standing self-supporting construction that is roofed, usually walled, and is intended for human occupancy (for example: a place of work or recreation) and/or habitation.

Subcode.Label: Non_Building_Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A free-standing self-supporting construction (for example: a large piece of equipment) designed to support human activities (for example: agriculture, manufacturing, or mining) but not intended for human occupancy and/or habitation (for example: a house, a bank, an office, or a stadium).

Subcode.Label: Building_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A relatively permanent structure, roofed and usually walled and designed for some particular use. (See also AL100)

Subcode.Label: Fab_Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used for the purpose of manufacturing COMPONENTs, which may be assembled on-site or elsewhere, to make a completed product; a fabrication building.

Subcode.Label: Gov_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING devoted to the act or process of administration of public policy in a political unit; a government building.

Subcode.Label: Capitol_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING in which a national or sub-national legislature meets; a capitol building.

Subcode.Label: Castle
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large fortified NON_EMPTY_SET of BUILDINGs with thick WALLs, usually dominating the surrounding TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION; a castle [SOED, "castle", I.1].

Subcode.Label: Gov_Admin_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING devoted to the act or process of administration of public policy in a political unit; a government building.

Subcode.Label: Hospital
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used to provide inpatient medical, surgical, or psychiatric care and treatment for the sick or the injured; a hospital.

Subcode.Label: House_of_Worship
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A place where religious worship is performed, especially a BUILDING designed for this purpose; a place of worship [SOED, "place of worship"]. EXAMPLES CHAPEL, CHURCH, MOSQUE, SYNAGOGUE.

Subcode.Label: Mil_Admin_Ops_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING devoted to the act or process of managing military forces or overseeing the conduct of military operations; a military operations building.

Subcode.Label: Museum
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING devoted to the acquisition, conservation, study, exhibition, and educational interpretation of OBJECTs having scientific, historical, or artistic value; a museum [AHD, "museum"].

Subcode.Label: Observatory
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A station that is equipped for observation and study.

Subcode.Label: Palace
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING serving, or that has previously served, as the official residence of a royal personage or high dignitary in a religious establishment or government; a palace [SOED, "palace", 1].

Subcode.Label: Police_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PUBLIC_SERVICE_STATION that serves as the headquarters of a unit of a police force and that is where those under arrest are first charged; a police station.

Subcode.Label: Prison
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING within which persons convicted or accused of crimes are confined; a penitentiary or correctional building.

Subcode.Label: Ranger_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING housing a warden employed to maintain and protect a FOREST or other natural REGION of a PLANETARY_SURFACE; a ranger station.

Subcode.Label: School
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used for instruction; a school building.

Subcode.Label: House
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING serving as a DWELLING for one or more HUMANs, especially for a family; a house [AHD, "house, 1.a"].

Subcode.Label: Multi_Unit_Dwelling
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used as a DWELLING by multiple groups of occupants; a multi-unit dwelling.

Subcode.Label: Cemetery_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING associated with a CEMETERY.

Subcode.Label: Farm_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING located on a FARM.

Subcode.Label: Greenhouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING, which is often constructed primarily of transparent MATERIAL (for example: glass or plastic), in which AIR_TEMPERATURE and RELATIVE_HUMIDITY can be controlled for the cultivation and/or protection of PLANTs; a greenhouse [SOED, "greenhouse", a].

Subcode.Label: Garage
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING or indoor space used to park or keep MOTOR_VEHICLEs; a parking garage.

Subcode.Label: Watermill_Gristmill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE equipped with water-driven EQUIPMENT for grinding grain into flour or meal; a water driven gristmill.

Subcode.Label: Wind_Tunnel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT through which AIR is forced at controlled velocities in order to study the effects of aerodynamic flow around airfoils, scale models, or other OBJECTs; a wind tunnel [AHD, "wind tunnel"].

Subcode.Label: Warehouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING in which goods or merchandise are stored; a warehouse [AHD, "warehouse", 1].

Subcode.Label: Roundhouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A circular BUILDING containing a RAILWAY_TURNTABLE; a roundhouse [AHD, "roundhouse", 1].

Subcode.Label: Railroad_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY used for the servicing, repair, and/or storage of RAIL_WAGONs and related EQUIPMENT.

Subcode.Label: Depot_Terminal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A RAILWAY_STATION or BUS_STATION, usually with an attached WAREHOUSE; a depot.

Subcode.Label: Admin_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING devoted to the act and/or process of administration or management.

Subcode.Label: AC_Maint_Shop
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING, usually located at an AERODROME, used for keeping AIRCRAFT in a condition of good repair and/or efficiency; an aircraft maintenance shop.

Subcode.Label: Hangar
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used for the storage of AIRCRAFT; an aircraft hangar [SOED, "hangar"].

Subcode.Label: Customs_House
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A GOVERNMENT_BUILDING serving as a CHECKPOINT where customs duties are collected and shipments or VEHICLEs are cleared for entering or leaving a country; a customs house.

Subcode.Label: Health_Office
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used in the diagnosis and care of outpatients; a health office or clinic.

Subcode.Label: Firing_Range
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY designated for the purpose of discharging firearms or detonating MUNITIONs; a weapons range, a firing range, or a gunnery range.

Subcode.Label: Post_Office
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PUBLIC_SERVICE_STATION where postal business (for example: where mail is handled and/or where stamps and other postal materials are sold) may be carried on; a post office.

Subcode.Label: Dormitory
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used to house CIVILIAN_PERSONNEL that is typically large, unadorned, and intended for relatively temporary occupancy; a dormitory.

Subcode.Label: Fire_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PUBLIC_SERVICE_STATION that houses both fire-fighting EQUIPMENT and PERSONNEL; a fire station [MWCD, "fire station"] or firehouse.

Subcode.Label: Jail
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A local DETENTION_FACILITY where the criminally accused are initially taken to be processed and await trial and where short (usually less than one year) sentences for criminal misconduct can be served; a jail.

Subcode.Label: Guardhouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A local DETENTION_FACILITY where the criminally accused are initially taken to be processed and await trial and where short (usually less than one year) sentences for criminal misconduct can be served; a jail.

Subcode.Label: Telephone_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A COMMUNICATION_STATION housing a SYSTEM of switches that establishes connections between individual telecommunication DEVICEs; a telecom switching station.

Subcode.Label: Church
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING functioning as a WORSHIP_PLACE for public, especially Christian, worship; a church [SOED, "church", 1].

Subcode.Label: Market
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open space or STRUCTURE where goods are offered for sale; a market [SOED, "market", 2].

Subcode.Label: Town_Hall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The MUNICIPAL_HALL of a TOWN.

Subcode.Label: Bank
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING housing an establishment for the deposit, custody, and issue of money; for making loans and discounts; and for making easier the exchange of funds by certificates, checks, and/or notes; a bank [SOED, "bank", n3.3].

Subcode.Label: Service_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING housing an establishment for the deposit, custody, and issue of money; for making loans and discounts; and for making easier the exchange of funds by certificates, checks, and/or notes; a bank [SOED, "bank", n3.3].

Subcode.Label: Yacht_Club
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The BUILDINGs, GROUNDS, and DOCKs of an organization that promotes and supports yachting, sailing, and boating; a nautical club, yacht club, or sailing club.

Subcode.Label: Public_Inn
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A RESTAURANT where lodging may be available; a public inn.

Subcode.Label: Restaurant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING or outdoor SITE where meals are served to the public; a restaurant [AHD, "restaurant"].

Subcode.Label: Observation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBSERVATION_STATION designed and equipped for making observations of astronomical, meteorological, or other natural phenomena; an observatory [SOED, "observatory", 1].

Subcode.Label: RD_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING supporting scientific experimentation or research, including scholarly investigation or inquiry, intended to ultimately result in commercial products; a science building.

Subcode.Label: University
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The BUILDINGs and GROUNDS of an institution offering special instruction in professional and/or technical subjects, which may also include FACILITYs for research and the award of advanced degrees; a university campus or college campus.

Subcode.Label: Courthouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING that houses the main offices of a county government; a county hall or court-house (US).

Subcode.Label: Legation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING in a foreign country that houses a diplomatic mission that ranks below an embassy; a legation building.

Subcode.Label: Mission
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A religious centre established in a REGION for missionary, evangelical, or humanitarian work; a mission [SOED, "mission", 4.b].

Subcode.Label: Chancery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING containing an office for public records; a chancery [SOED, "chancery", 3].

Subcode.Label: Ambassadorial_Residence
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING serving as the DWELLING of a diplomatic official of the highest rank appointed and accredited as representative in residence by one government or sovereign to another; an ambassadorial residence.

Subcode.Label: Embassy
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING housing the office of an ambassador and/or the ambassador's staff; an embassy [AHD, "embassy", 1].

Subcode.Label: Consulate
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING housing the residence and/or official premises of an official appointed by a government to reside in a foreign country, represent its commercial interests, and assist its citizens there; a consulate.

Subcode.Label: Guard_House
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small enclosed BUILDING accommodating a guard or serving as a DETENTION_FACILITY; a guardhouse [SOED, "guardhouse"].

Subcode.Label: Guard_Shack
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small enclosed ROOM accommodating a guard or serving as a DETENTION_FACILITY; a guardroom [SOED, "guardroom"].

Subcode.Label: Kennel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE used for the breeding, training, or boarding of dogs; a kennel [AHD, "kennel", 3].

Subcode.Label: Oil_Mill_Vegetable
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING that houses EQUIPMENT that releases the oils of vegetable seeds by pressing and/or grinding; a vegetable oil mill.

Subcode.Label: Aerator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE for aerating WATER by either passing AIR through WATER or passing WATER through AIR.

Subcode.Label: Carpentry
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING in which wooden OBJECTs are manufactured or repaired; a carpentry building or a carpentry shop.

Subcode.Label: Sawmill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING where LOGs are processed into lumber; a sawmill.

Subcode.Label: Kiln_Oven
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An oven for hardening, burning, or drying MATERIALs (for example: grain, meal, and/or clay), especially a brick-lined oven used to bake or fire ceramics; a kiln [AHD, "kiln"].

Subcode.Label: Signalman_House
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A manned STRUCTURE located adjacent to a RAILWAY that displays control information to passing TRAINs; a signalman house.

Subcode.Label: Harbor_Master_Office
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Marine_Police
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A POLICE_STATION that serves a HARBOUR or coastal REGION; a marine police station.

Subcode.Label: Rescue
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Port_Control
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Maritime_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Lighthouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A distinctive STRUCTURE exhibiting one or more LIGHTs designed to serve as an AID_TO_NAVIGATION; a lighthouse.

Subcode.Label: Power_Generation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING and associated EQUIPMENT used for the generation of electric power; a power generation building.

Subcode.Label: Filtration_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE containing layers of MATERIAL used to filter or aerate WATER; a water treatment structure.

Subcode.Label: Newspaper_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used in the printing, collating, storage, or distribution of a newspaper; a newspaper plant.

Subcode.Label: Telephone_Exchange
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE housing a central SYSTEM of switches and other EQUIPMENT that establishes connections between individual telecommunication DEVICEs (for example: a telephone); a main telecom exchange.

Subcode.Label: Auditorium
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large BUILDING for public meetings and/or performances; an auditorium.

Subcode.Label: Opera_House
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING that houses a THEATRE designed chiefly for the performance of operas.

Subcode.Label: Processing_Treatment
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING that is used for the changing or refining of a particular MATERIAL; a processing or treatment building.

Subcode.Label: Pumphouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING or ROOM housing pumps for raising, compressing, or transferring fluids; a pump room or pump house (US).

Subcode.Label: Mobile_Home
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A trailer that is used as a DWELLING, has no permanent foundation, and is designed to be easily moved; a mobile home [MWCD, "mobile home"].

Subcode.Label: Weather_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBSERVATION_STATION where meteorological data are gathered, recorded, and released; a weather station.

Subcode.Label: Dependents_Housing
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Railroad_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING or stopping place along a RAILWAY for taking on and letting off passengers or for servicing; a railway station.

Subcode.Label: Hotel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used to provide lodging, and usually meals and other services, for travellers and other paying guests; a hotel [AHD, "hotel"].

Subcode.Label: Diplomatic_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING that houses and/or supports the activities of an ambassador; a diplomatic building.

Subcode.Label: Trading_Post
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE occupied for purposes of trade, especially in a remote and/or unsettled REGION; a trading post [SOED, "trading post"].

Subcode.Label: Shed
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A relatively small BUILDING, which usually has one or more open sides, that is typically used for storage; a shed.

Subcode.Label: Battery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An emplacement for one or more pieces of FIELD_ARTILLERY; an artillery battery [SOED, "battery", II.4].

Subcode.Label: Medical_Center
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY devoted to medical research and/or the practice of medicine.

Subcode.Label: Municipal_Hall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING that contains the offices of the public officials of a local political unit; a municipal hall.

Subcode.Label: Oil_Facilities_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING involved in the production or distribution of PETROLEUM.

Subcode.Label: Outbuilding
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small BUILDING that is separate from but is located near a main BUILDING; an outbuilding.

Subcode.Label: Paper_Pulp_Mill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY for processing natural fibres (for example: wood) into flexible sheets or rolls of paper by deposit from an aqueous suspension; a paper-mill.

Subcode.Label: Reformatory
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used for the discipline, reformation, and training of young and/or first offenders; a reformatory building.

Subcode.Label: Sanitarium
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY that houses an institution for the treatment of chronic diseases or for medically supervised recuperation; a sanatorium.

Subcode.Label: Tracking_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE with an associated AERIAL used for tracking, control, transmission, and/or reception of signals from ARTIFICIAL_SATELLITEs; a satellite ground station.

Subcode.Label: Seminary
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY used as a school, especially a theological school, for the training of priests, ministers, or rabbis; a seminary [AHD, "seminary", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Sr_Citizen_Home
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A residential BUILDING housing a group of elderly HUMANs; a senior citizens home.

Subcode.Label: Shipyard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE where VESSELs are built or repaired; a shipyard [SOED, "shipyard"].

Subcode.Label: Sportsplex
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An arena with tiered seats or terraces for spectators of athletic or sporting events [SOED, "stadium", 3].

Subcode.Label: Steel_Mill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY for the production of fabricated structural steel products (for example: girders and/or plates); a steel mill.

Subcode.Label: Weigh_Scale
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT, which is usually located alongside a ROAD, that is used to determine the weight of GROUND_VEHICLEs; a scale.

Subcode.Label: House_of_Worship-NC
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A place where religious worship is performed, especially a BUILDING designed for this purpose; a place of worship [SOED, "place of worship"]. EXAMPLES CHAPEL, CHURCH, MOSQUE, SYNAGOGUE.

Subcode.Label: Hostel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used to provide supervised, inexpensive lodging for travellers, especially young travellers; a hostel [AHD, "hostel", 1].

Subcode.Label: Factory
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING containing EQUIPMENT for use in manufacturing; a factory [SOED, "factory", 3].

Subcode.Label: Motel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used to provide lodging for motorists in ROOMs usually having direct access to an open VEHICLE_LOT; a motel [AHD, "motel"], motor court, or motor lodge.

Subcode.Label: Community_Center
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used for recreational exercise and minor sports competitions, which typically serves a small TOWN, community, or local BUILT_UP_REGION; a community recreation building or a community centre.

Subcode.Label: City_Hall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The MUNICIPAL_HALL of a CITY.

Subcode.Label: Automobile_Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A HEAVY_INDUSTRIAL_FACILITY used for the purpose of manufacturing MOTOR_VEHICLEs; an automotive plant.

Subcode.Label: Armory
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING for storing arms and military EQUIPMENT, especially one serving as headquarters for reserve MILITARY_PERSONNEL; an armoury [AHD, "armory", 1.b].

Subcode.Label: Shopping_Center
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A group of RETAIL_FACILITYs, often including RESTAURANTs and other businesses, having a common VEHICLE_LOT; a shopping centre [AHD, "shopping center"].

Subcode.Label: Correctional_Institute
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more CORRECTIONAL_BUILDINGs; a correctional facility.

Subcode.Label: Repair_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used for restoring broken and/or damaged goods (for example: EQUIPMENT) to sound condition; a repair building.

Subcode.Label: Machinery_Shed
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Astronomical_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE used for the scientific study of matter in SPACE, especially the LOCATIONs, dimensions, distribution, motion, composition, energy, and evolution of CELESTIAL_BODYs or celestial phenomena; an astronomical station.

Subcode.Label: Theater
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING, ROOM, or outdoor STRUCTURE used for the presentation of plays, films, or other dramatic performances; a theatre [AHD, "theater", 1].

Subcode.Label: Library
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING in which literary and artistic materials (for example: books, periodicals, newspapers, pamphlets, prints, records, and/or tapes) are kept for reading, reference, and/or lending; a library [AHD, "library", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Airport_Terminal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING located at an AERODROME used for disembarking and/or taking on passengers or CARGO; an aerodrome terminal.

Subcode.Label: Bus_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE, usually in a TOWN or CITY, that serves as a BUS_STOP, especially for long-distance buses or coaches; a bus station [SOED, "bus station"].

Subcode.Label: Pilot_Office
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Pilot_Lookout
Subcode.Concept_Definition: N/A

Subcode.Label: Commercial_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used to conduct business activities; a commercial building.

Subcode.Label: Fort
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A permanently fortified STRUCTURE that may be stationed with MILITARY_PERSONNEL and is generally walled or heavily fenced with overwatch positions; a fort.

Subcode.Label: Blockhouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A military FORTIFICATION constructed of sturdy MATERIALs (for example: concrete) and designed with WALL_LOOPHOLEs; a blockhouse [SOED, "blockhouse", a].

Subcode.Label: Martello_Tower
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A stone TOWER defending a COAST or HARBOUR and usually including a gun platform, ammunition magazine, and accommodations for a garrison; a Martello tower.

Subcode.Label: Guard_Tower
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An elevated enclosed BUILDING including one or more GUARDROOMs; a guard tower.

Subcode.Label: Jetway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An enclosed, movable connector which extends from an airport terminal gate to an airplane, allowing passengers to board and disembark without going outside.

Subcode.Label: Fire_and_Police_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PUBLIC_SERVICE_STATION that houses both a FIRE_STATION and a POLICE_STATION.

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An INDUSTRIAL_WORKS for purifying ores (for example: copper and/or silver) and extracting from them various metal and chemical products; an ore refinery.

Subcode.Label: Fire_Hydrant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An apparatus for drawing water directly from a main, especially alongside a street or road, consisting of a pipe with one or more nozzles or spouts, to which a hose of a fire-engine may be attached.

Subcode.Label: Building_Addition
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A supplemental portion of a building which rises from the roof but is not considered to be part of the general roof line.

Subcode.Label: Shed
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A storage facility usually characterized by one or more open sides, support pillars and a roof.

Subcode.Label: Built-Up_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area containing a concentration of buildings and other structures.

Subcode.Label: Built-up_Area-Hist
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area that constitutes a concentration of historical buildings or other historical structures within a built up area.

Subcode.Label: Populated_Place
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A named area where people live and/or work.

Subcode.Label: Cairn
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A heap of stones piled up as a memorial or a landmark. (See also AL090 and AL130)

Subcode.Label: Cemetery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of land for burying the dead.

Subcode.Label: Grave
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site where a corpse is buried.

Subcode.Label: Tomb
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure within which a corpse is entombed.

Subcode.Label: Cliff_Dwelling
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A dwelling built in the recesses of cliffs. (See also AL250)

Subcode.Label: Complex_Outline
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An outline delimiting an area in which two or more like features have the same function.

Subcode.Label: Display_Sign
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An upright panel used to convey visual information. (See also AL080)

Subcode.Label: Dragon_Teeth
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Regularly spaced concrete or metal barriers laid in single or multiple rows to prevent vehicle movement.

Subcode.Label: Minefield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site laid with explosive mines.

Subcode.Label: Fence
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A man-made barrier of relatively light structure used as an enclosure or boundary. (See also AL260)

Subcode.Label: Flagstaff
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A staff or pole on which a flag is raised.

Subcode.Label: Gallery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A sunken or cut passageway along a transportation route in mountainous regions constructed to protect vehicles from the elements. A series of openings on one side may be present for light or ventilation.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Gantry
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A frame structure raised on side supports so as to span over or around something. (See also AL050)

Subcode.Label: Grave_Marker
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A marker indicating an individual grave site. (See also AL025 and AL130)

Subcode.Label: Homogeneous_Radar_Sig_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A cluster of structures that combine to form a homogeneous area when grouped according to a common radar reflectance and a common height value.

Subcode.Label: Hut
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small, simple free-standing (detached) self-contained residence usually having only a single multi-function room.

Subcode.Label: Hut
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small simple or crude house or shelter. (See also AL015)

Subcode.Label: Cabin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building in a remote or wilderness area.

Subcode.Label: Settlement
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A concentration of small dwellings.

Subcode.Label: Light_Standard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure serving as a support for lighting.

Subcode.Label: Calvary_Cross
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure, mounted on a pedestal, composed of an upright member with a shorter horizontal member centered at approximately two thirds of the height of the upright member.

Subcode.Label: Missile_Site_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area with related facilities for storing and launching missiles.

Subcode.Label: ABM
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE and related FACILITYs for storing and launching ABM MISSILEs; a missile site.

Subcode.Label: ICBM

Subcode.Label: IRBM

Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE and related FACILITYs for storing and launching MRBM MISSILEs; a missile site.

Subcode.Label: SSM
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE and related FACILITYs for storing and launching SSM MISSILEs; a missile site.

Subcode.Label: SAM
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE and related FACILITYs for storing and launching SAM MISSILEs; a missile site.

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE and related FACILITYs for storing and launching other type of MISSILEs; a missile site.

Subcode.Label: Anti_Aircraft_Artillery_Site
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site and related facilities (for example: buildings and/or radar equipment) for storing and launching anti-aircraft artillery.

Subcode.Label: Monument
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure erected or maintained as a memorial to a person or event. (See also AL025 and AL090)

Subcode.Label: Native_Settlement
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A concentration of native dwellings, generally of the hut type, which are not usually of substantial construction.

Subcode.Label: Particle_Accelerator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An apparatus for imparting high velocities to charged particles.

Subcode.Label: Telescope
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An apparatus used for observing distant objects or phenomena.

Subcode.Label: Astronomical_Observatory
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building designed and equipped (for example: with a telescope) for making observations of celestial objects (including the earth in relation to them), of space, and of the universe as a whole.

Subcode.Label: Overhead
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An undelineated obstruction location such as underpasses, overhead pipelines, building overhangs, and other covered traveled ways.

Subcode.Label: Pipeline_Crossing_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A traversable site extending across a pipeline that acts as a passageway for cross-country movement of vehicles or troops.

Subcode.Label: Plaza
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open area which serves as a public square in a city or town. (See also AK120)

Subcode.Label: Courtyard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open area that is open to the sky and surrounded by walls or buildings forming the precincts of a larger facility (for example: an extended house, a castle, or a homestead), often in the form of an area that is enclosed by a single building.

Subcode.Label: Retail_Stand
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small structure that stands alone, and is designated for the purpose of supplying a product (for example: souvenirs, magazines, snacks or refreshments) or service (for example: a shoe shine) to passers-by.

Subcode.Label: Ramp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An inclined plane usually man-made for moving between two levels. (See also BB240)

Subcode.Label: Ruins
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The deteriorated remains of an unspecified structure. (See also AL012)

Subcode.Label: Historic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Site or area declared to be of national or provincial historical significance or interest, maintained for the public.

Subcode.Label: Shanty_Town
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A section of a built-up area consisting chiefly of densely packed shacks and having few, if any, streets and no public facilities.

Subcode.Label: Tent_Encampment
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An encampment of people housed in tents.

Subcode.Label: Snow_Shed
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A shelter build to protect a section of road or railroad from snow/rock slides.

Subcode.Label: Trans_Route_Protect_Struct
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure built over and/or along a transportation route designed to prevent damage to, or blockage of, the route from rock slides, snow slides and/or weather phenomena.

Subcode.Label: Steeple
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure usually ending in a sharp point and which may be erected on a roof of a building.

Subcode.Label: Tower-NC
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A relatively tall structure which may be used for observation, support, or storage, etc. (See also AF030, AM080, AQ060, and BI050)

Subcode.Label: Tower_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A relatively tall, narrow structure that may either stand alone or may form part of another structure.

Subcode.Label: Bridge
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of Tower, a Bridge tower.

Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of Tower, a Mooring_Tower.

Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of Tower, a Powerline_Tower.

Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of Tower, a Microwave tower.

Subcode.Label: Undergrd_Dwelling
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Underground living quarters. (See also AL040)

Subcode.Label: Wall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A solid man-made barrier of heavy material used as an enclosure or boundary or for protection. (See also AL070)

Subcode.Label: Industrial_Farm
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An estate or large farm operating on the plantation economy model in which the farm operates as a single economic unit whose operations are based on agricultural mass production of a few staple crops (for example: cotton, tobacco, sugar cane, bananas, and/or rubber) that are typically not indigenous to the region.

Subcode.Label: Religious_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility, building, structure or site that was designed and designated to be used for religious activities.

Subcode.Label: Space_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility that is used to support space related activities (for example: services such as assembly, launching or recovery of spacecraft or managing flight operations).

Subcode.Label: Country_House
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A house that is large and impressive enough to be considered a mansion (for example: having several dozen rooms) and is located on a large estate in the country and is occupied as the private residence of the landowner.

Subcode.Label: Castle
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large fortified building or group of buildings that has thick walls, battlements, and often a moat.

Subcode.Label: Tethered_Balloon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A balloon that is tethered to the ground at an anchoring device (for example: a ring and pad) or substantial structure (for example: a mooring tower).

Subcode.Label: Depot
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area used for the storage of products or supplies. (See also AB000)

Subcode.Label: Container
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A closed structure used for the storage and containment of solid, liquid or gaseous materials. (See also AM020, AM070, and AM080)

Subcode.Label: Grain_Silo
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An enclosed container, used for storing grain or fodder. (See also AM011, AM070, and AM080)

Subcode.Label: Grain_Elevator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tall structure, equipped for loading, unloading, processing and storing grain.

Subcode.Label: Timber_Yard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open area for the storage of wooden lumber and timbers.

Subcode.Label: Mineral_Pile
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A man-made heap of mining or quarrying products excluding waste materials. (See also AB000)

Subcode.Label: Material_Pile
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A man-made heap of material(s) of unspecified nature.

Subcode.Label: Storage_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE intended for storing MATERIALs or products; a storage structure.

Subcode.Label: Soft_Standing
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open TRACT without a prepared SURFACE of pavement or gravel used for parking and/or storing purposes

Subcode.Label: Hard_Standing
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open TRACT with a prepared SURFACE of pavement or gravel used for parking and/or storing purposes

Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FARM_BUILDING that is used to store hay, grain, and implements and/or to house NON_HUMAN_ANIMALs; a barn [SOED, "barn", A.1] [SOED, "barn", A.2].

Subcode.Label: Warehouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING in which goods or merchandise are stored; a warehouse [AHD, "warehouse", 1].

Subcode.Label: Warehouse_Specialized
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING in which specialized goods or merchandise are stored; a warehouse [AHD, "warehouse", 1].

Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE intended for storing diesel fuel.

Subcode.Label: Gasoline
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE intended for storing gasoline.

Subcode.Label: Oil
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE intended for storing oil.

Subcode.Label: Water
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE intended for storing water.

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE intended for storing materials other than those listed above.

Subcode.Label: Munition_Storage_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility for the storage of munitions (for example: bombs, missiles, warheads, mines or ammunition).

Subcode.Label: Tank
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A container used for the storage of liquids or gases. (See also AM011, AM020, and AM080)

Subcode.Label: Tank_Farm
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tract of land occupied by large-capacity tanks in which petroleum, natural gas, or liquid petrochemicals are stored.

Subcode.Label: Fuel_Storage_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A facility for the storage of fuel (for example: jet fuel, gasoline, or diesel oil).

Subcode.Label: Water_Tower
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An elevated container and its supporting structure used to hold water. (See also AM011, AM020, and AM070)

Subcode.Label: Silo
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large storage structure used for storing loose materials.

Subcode.Label: Transshipment_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A complex of buildings, associated facilities, roads, and adapted areas used for transshipment of freight between the same or different kinds of transport.

Subcode.Label: Railroad_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: One or more railway tracks comprising a network that is operated for the conveyance of passengers and/or goods.

Subcode.Label: Car-Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs; a Car-Line railway, or a Car-Line railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Monorail
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one RAILWAY_TRACK; a Monorail railway, or a Monorail railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Subway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An underground LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs; a Subway railway, or a Subway railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Logging
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs that is used for logging operations; a Logging railway, or a Logging railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Miniature
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A miniature LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs; a Miniature railway, or a Miniature railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Rapid_Transit_Route
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A rapid transit LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs; a Rapid_Transit_Route railway, or a Rapid_Transit_Route railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Marine_Railroad
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs that is used for marine operations;; a Marine_Railroad railway, or a Marine_Railroad railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Tramway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs that is used for streetcars or cablecars; a Tramway railway, or a Tramway railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Inclined_Railway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Ainclined LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs; a Inclined_Railway railway, or a Inclined_Railway railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Main_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A maain or primary LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs; a Main_Line railway, or a Main_Line railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Branch_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A branch or secondary LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs; a Branch_Line railway, or a Branch_Line railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Railroad_in_Road
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE consisting of one or more RAILWAY_TRACKs embedded in a road; a Railroad_in_Road railway, or a Railroad_in_Road railroad (US).

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE type other than those listed above

Subcode.Label: Railway_Track
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A rail or set of parallel rails on which a train, tram, or rail wagon runs.

Subcode.Label: Railroad_Siding
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A stretch of railroad tracks connected to the main track by switch(es) - used for temporary storage and loading/unloading.

Subcode.Label: Railroad_Yard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A system of tracks within defined limits, and associated features, provided for loading/unloading and assembling trains.

Subcode.Label: Railhead
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A location where materials can be loaded or unloaded from railroad wagons.

Subcode.Label: Railroad_Turntable
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A rotating platform with railroad tracks used for turning locomotives or cars/carriages.

Subcode.Label: Roundhouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A circular or semicircular building, with a railway turntable in the centre, used for storing and/or repairing railway locomotives.

Subcode.Label: Railroad_Switch
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A location on a railroad at which rails may be switched to permit access to another line.

Subcode.Label: Railway_Signal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A signal used to control traffic on a railway.

Subcode.Label: Cart_Track
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An unimproved roadway.

Subcode.Label: Interchange_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A connection designed to provide traffic access from one road to another.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Railroad Network Lineal Figure Pt, Road Network Lineal Figure Pt

Subcode.Label: Cloverleaf
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interchange between two major highways that allows traffic to change from one to the other without requiring any left turns or crossings and that from above resembles a 4-leaf clover

Subcode.Label: Diamond
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interchange between two major highways that allows traffic to change from one to the other without requiring any left turns or crossings and that from above resembles a diamond

Subcode.Label: Fork
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The point where a road or river divides into two or more parts

Subcode.Label: Roundabout
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A road junction at which traffic moves in one direction round a central island to reach one of the roads converging on it.

Subcode.Label: Staggered_Ramp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A short section of road which allows vehicles to enter or exit a freeway. (staggered)

Subcode.Label: Standard_Ramp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A short section of road which allows vehicles to enter or exit a freeway. (standard)

Subcode.Label: Symmetrical_Ramps
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A short section of road which allows vehicles to enter or exit a freeway. (symmetrical)

Subcode.Label: Trumpet
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interchange traditionally used where one expressway terminates at another expressway; it involves at least one loop ramp connecting traffic either entering or leaving the terminating expressway with the far lanes of the continuous expressway.

Subcode.Label: Turban
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interchange (known as a "whirlpool" in the UK). The turbine/whirlpool interchange requires fewer levels while retaining semi-directional ramps throughout and has the left-turning ramps sweep around the center of the interchange in a spiral pattern.

Subcode.Label: Wye
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A wye interchange is where one freeway terminates at another freeway with the same general directional alignment. The trunk of the terminating highway merges with the trunk of the continuous highway; vehicles traveling into the interchange may only exit traveling in the same direction. This type of interchange is often used for bypass routes, and is named for the shape the two highways' confluence makes when drawn on a map.

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interchange-type other than those listed above.

Subcode.Label: Road_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A generic term that refers to an open way on land between two places maintained for vehicular use. Roads consist of one, or sometimes two, roadways, each with one or more lanes and also any associated sidewalks

Subcode.Label: Street
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A low-capacity paved public road in a city, town, or village, onto which people and/or vehicles can move about and interact with one another. Consists of 1 or 2 lanes.

Subcode.Label: Rapid_Transit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Aroad used for the fast transportation of passengers (as by subway) in urban areas.

Subcode.Label: Laneway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Also known as Driveway. A narrow street or alley running behind urban buildings, especially houses. Typically is a private road for local vehicle access to one or a small group of structures, and is owned and maintained by an individual or group.

Subcode.Label: Service_Lane
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Also known as Alley or Alleyway. A narrow street or alley running behind urban buildings, especially houses or stores.

Subcode.Label: Backroad
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A secondary type of road, usually found in rural areas, undivided, with 1-2 lanes, usually unpaved (dirt or gravel)

Subcode.Label: Collector
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of road, termed for its low-to-medium capacity and its urban setting. The primary function of an Collector is to deliver traffic from Streets to Arteries. Typically 2 lanes, rarely 4 lanes

Subcode.Label: Artery_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of road, termed for its high-capacity and its urban setting. The primary function of an arterial road is to deliver traffic from collector roads to Highways.

Subcode.Label: Artery_Major
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An artery with 6 lanes or more, usually divided.

Subcode.Label: Artery_Minor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An artery with less than 6 lanes, usually divided.

Subcode.Label: Highway_Undivided_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of road, consisting of a single roadway, termed for its high-capacity and high speed. Its primary function is to interconnect cities. Also known as expressways, motorways, freeways, autobahn, autoroute, thruways, toolway.

Subcode.Label: Highway_Undivided_Major
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An undivided highway with 4 lanes or more

Subcode.Label: Highway_Undivided_Minor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An undivided highway with less than 4 lanes

Subcode.Label: Highway_Divided_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A type of road, consisting of a two or more roadways, termed for its high-capacity, high speed. Its primary function is to interconnect cities. All traffic flow and ingress/egress are regulated and no crossings at grade-level. Also known as expressways, motorways, freeways, autobahn, autoroute, thruways, toolway.

Subcode.Label: Highway_Divided_Major
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A divided highway with 6 lanes or more

Subcode.Label: Highway_Divided_Minor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A divided highway with less than 6 lanes

Subcode.Label: Lane
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A linear portion of a roadway surface marked out for use by a single line of vehicles in such a way as to control and guide drivers for the purpose of reducing traffic conflicts

Subcode.Label: Street_Major
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A wide street consisting of one wide lane or 2 lanes of average width.

Subcode.Label: Street_Minor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A narrow street usually consisting of 1 lane

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A road type other than those listed above

Subcode.Label: Road_Ramp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A section of a road interchange connecting two or more roads at different levels by means of an inclined roadway.

Subcode.Label: Motorway_Ramp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A section of a road interchange connecting two or more roads at different levels by means of an inclined roadway.

Subcode.Label: Trunk_Ramp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A section of a road interchange connecting two or more roads at different levels by means of an inclined roadway.

Subcode.Label: Gate
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A barrier which controls passage to a road, railroad, tunnel, or bridge.

Subcode.Label: Barrier
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A permanent obstruction placed across a route to prevent vehicular traffic.

Subcode.Label: Trail
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A path worn by the passage of people or animals.

Subcode.Label: Drove
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Wide track on the land's surface due to the regular movement of animal herds (e.g. sheep, cattle).

Subcode.Label: Cableway_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Cables which are strung between elevated supports as part of a conveyor system on which cars, buckets, or other carrier units are suspended. (Superseeded by Revised Cableway AT041 which now covers this concept)

Subcode.Label: Cableway_Pylon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tower supporting steel cables which convey cars, buckets, or other suspended carrier units.

Subcode.Label: Mast
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A straight piece of timber or a hollow cylinder of wood or metal set up vertically, or nearly so.

Subcode.Label: Boardwalk
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A walkway made of wooden planks. (See also BB140)

Subcode.Label: Sidewalk
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A paved or improved pedestrian path, typically located adjacent and parallel to a street or road.

Subcode.Label: Curb
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A border of concrete, asphalt or stone forming part of a gutter along the edge of a street or road.

Subcode.Label: Bridge_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure that connects two locations and provides for the passage of a transportation route (for example: a road or a railway) over a terrain obstacle (for example: a waterbody, a gully, and/or a road).
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Arch_Open
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An Arch_Open-type STRUCTURE that connects two LOCATIONs and provides for the passage of a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE over a TERRAIN_OBSTACLE (for example: a WATERBODY, a GULLY, and/or a ROAD); a bridge. A bridge consists of a SET of two or more BRIDGE_PIERs or BRIDGE_TOWERs joined by BRIDGE_SPANs.
