Subcode.Label: Cleared_Way
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A man-made clearing in a cultural area or through a stand of trees, designed to provide access for a road, railroad, pipeline, or power transmission line, or for boundary demarcation, survey line-of-sight, or to impede the progress of forest fires.

Subcode.Label: Grove
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small wood or similar collection of trees growing closely together.

Subcode.Label: Forest_Clearing
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A site in a forest or wood(s) that has been cleared, often for slash and burn agriculture and/or as a result of clear-cutting logging.

Subcode.Label: Rainforest
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A dense forest in an area of high rainfall with little seasonal variation, and whose canopy is usually closed (allowing only filtered sunlight to reach the ground).

Subcode.Label: Marsh
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of wet, often spongy ground that is subject to frequent or tidal inundations, but not considered to be continually under water. It is characterized by the growth of non woody plants and by the lack of trees. (Nautical Chart Manual, US National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration - NOAA, 1992) (See also BH090, BH095, and ED020)

Subcode.Label: Swamp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A low lying saturated area covered with water all or most of the year, where accumulating dead vegetation does not rapidly decay. It can exist on flat-lying areas created by certain geomorphic environments. The vegetation mainly consists of hydrophytic trees and/or scrubs whose roots are adapted to wet conditions, with an open to very dense canopy closure. (See also BH090, BH095, and ED010)

Subcode.Label: Mangrove_Swamp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A dense thicket of mangrove that is subject to tidal inundation and forming a muddy swamp.

Subcode.Label: Taiga
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A swampy coniferous forest of high northern latitudes, especially that between the tundra and steppes of Siberia.

Subcode.Label: Vegetation_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT covered by a mixture of woody and non-woody PLANTs; a mixed vegetation land.

Subcode.Label: Cranberry
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT primarily covered by cranberry.

Subcode.Label: Peat
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT primarily covered by compacted deposit of partially decomposed organic debris, usually saturated with water.

Subcode.Label: Herb_or_Shrub
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A low growing, multi-stemmed woody PLANT; a shrub [AHD, "shrub"].

Subcode.Label: Reed
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT primarily covered by tall slender plants with jointed stalks that grows in marshes and other wet areas.

Subcode.Label: Moss
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PLANT of the class Musci, comprising small bryophtes with scale-like leaves usually spirally arranged, with a spore-capsule usually opening by a lid, which grow in crowded masses in BOGs or on SURFACEs; or any of certain ALGAs, LICHENs, PTERIDOPHYTEs, or flowering PLANTs resembling moss in habit; moss [SOED, "moss", II 3] or a moss-like plant.

Subcode.Label: Kelp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_FLOOR_REGION covered with a significant concentration of kelp; a kelp bed.

Subcode.Label: Sea_Weed
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of large green, brown, or dark red VEGETATION (for example: kelp and/or seaweed) growing in a salt WATER, typically cold, environment.

Subcode.Label: Sea_Grass
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of an underwater ocean grass with long thick blades that is harvested and processed into a material, similar to twine or jute, used for making baskets and matting

Subcode.Label: Saragasso
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of a brown seaweed with berry-like air bladders, typically floating in large masses.

Subcode.Label: Other
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION with vegetation other than those listed above

Subcode.Label: Logging_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of forest or vegetation being exploited for lumber resources.

Subcode.Label: No_Vegetation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Ground or land with little (less than 5 percent) or no vegetation.

Subcode.Label: Desert
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An arid and treeless uncultivated sparsely populated tract of land.

Subcode.Label: Garden
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A piece of ground (often enclosed) where fruits, flowers, herbs, or vegetables are cultivated.

Subcode.Label: Bank_Vegetation_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region along the edge of a body of water or watercourse generally dominated by riparian vegetation.

Subcode.Label: Economic_Reserve
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tract of public land reserved for future use and/or restricted as to present use.

Subcode.Label: Boundary-Admin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line of demarcation between controlled areas.

Subcode.Label: Area-Admin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area controlled by administrative authority.

Subcode.Label: Geopolitical_Entity
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region controlled by a political community having an organized government and possessing internal and external sovereignity, most often as a State but sometimes having a dependent relationship on another political authority or a special sovereignity status.

Subcode.Label: Administrative_Division
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A subordinate administrative division (for example: a (US) state, a (UK) county, a (US) township, a (CA) province, a (FR) arrondissement, a (CH) canton, a (GE) laender and a (FR) commune) of a geopolitical entity (for example: a State).

Subcode.Label: Access_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A zone between a contact zone and the first possible clearing line (road, towing path, passable road bank crest). (See also FA041)

Subcode.Label: Sovereign_State
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region where a community (people) has the full sovereignty about a national territory.

Subcode.Label: Territory_Special_Status
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A territory, which is not an independent sovereign State nor a regular part of a sovereign State.

Subcode.Label: Contaminated_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region whose prevailing natural conditions have been degraded through contamination by harmful or objectionable substances.

Subcode.Label: Firing_Range
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open area designated for the purpose of discharging or detonating firearms.

Subcode.Label: Armistice_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line established by opposing political groups as a result of cessation of hostilities.

Subcode.Label: Cease-Fire_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line along which active hostilities are suspended.

Subcode.Label: Claim_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A limit of an area which is unilaterally claimed by one political group without consent or negotiation with another.

Subcode.Label: Contact_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Terrain area 3 metres wide limited on the water side by the contact between land and water (under average level of water condition). (See also FA005)

Subcode.Label: Contact_Zone_Stanag2256
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A terrain strip extending from 2 metres below to 6 metres inland of the Mean Water Line.

Subcode.Label: Mandate_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line established to regulate matters between nations or groups over a specific area or territory.

Subcode.Label: Boundary-Defacto
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An existing line of separation not officially recognized by various governments.

Subcode.Label: Demilitarized_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where military activity is prohibited.

Subcode.Label: National_Park
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Extensive area of a particular nature, that has been defined by law and that is to be protected as a whole. It meets the prerequisites of a nature reserve for the largest part and has been influenced by man at most only to a small extent .

Subcode.Label: Nature_Reserve
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area that has been legally defined and whose nature and landscape requires special protection, be it in part or as a whole, in order to preserve symbioses or biotypes of specific wildlife animals or plants, for scientific reasons or reasons of natural or geographic history, or because of their rareness, uniqueness or outstanding beauty.

Subcode.Label: Protected_Water
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Protected area of water collection facilities with restricted use in order to protect the water above and under ground from being polluted.

Subcode.Label: Prospecting_Grid
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A grid established for the collection of geophysical data within an area.

Subcode.Label: Geophysical_Data_Track_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A track along which a series of geophysical data observations are distributed.

Subcode.Label: Test_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Area for the testing of technical products.

Subcode.Label: Date_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line generally coinciding with the 180th meridian, modified to avoid land, and designated as the place where each calendar day begins.

Subcode.Label: Boundary
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line separating two geographic areas from each other.

Subcode.Label: Training_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area reserved for training.

Subcode.Label: Zone_of_Occupation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area temporarily held and controlled by a foreign military force.

Subcode.Label: Conservation_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of land and/or sea especially dedicated to the protection and maintenance of biological diversity, and of natural and associated cultural resources, and managed through legal or other effective means.

Subcode.Label: Military_Administrative_Unit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area which is the responsibility of territorial commands.

Subcode.Label: Noise_Control_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area surrounding commercial airports with scheduled air services and/or military airfields earmarked for the operation of aircraft with jet engines, where building restrictions may be enforced in order to protect the public from dangers, major disadvantages and major irritation due to aircraft noise.

Subcode.Label: Maritime_Boundary
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line where on either side certain activities or factors of significance to navigation and/or operation apply.

Subcode.Label: Maritime_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area in which certain activities or factors of significance to navigation and/or operation apply.

Subcode.Label: Dumping_Ground
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A sea area where dredged material or other potentially more harmful material (for example: explosives or chemical waste) is deliberately deposited.

Subcode.Label: Dredged_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the bottom of a body of water (for example: a channel) which has been deepened by dredging.

Subcode.Label: Pond
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A structure separating the basins of a fish pond, a reservoir or a liquid waste pond.

Subcode.Label: Restricted_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area in which certain aspects of navigation are restricted.

Subcode.Label: Caution_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Generally, an area where the mariner has to be made aware of circumstances influencing the safety of navigation.

Subcode.Label: Diving_Location
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A location where civilian diving activities take place.

Subcode.Label: TSS_System
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Complex feature with possible components made of many simple features and complex features BC099, BC098 and FC166. (Superseded by Traffic Separation Scheme (FC041); complex features no longer needed.

Subcode.Label: TSS
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A maritime routing measure that separates opposing streams of traffic by appropriate means.

Subcode.Label: Inshore_Traffic_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A routeing measure comprising a designated area between the landward boundary of a traffic separation scheme and the adjacent coast, to be used in accordance with the provisions of the International Regulations for Preventing Collisions at Sea.

Subcode.Label: Unsurveyed_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region for which no bathymetric survey information is available.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A geographically defined part of a waterbody (for example: the sea or other navigable waters).

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Morphology_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region of a waterbody, either surface or subsurface, that is homogeneous with respect to form.

Subcode.Label: Naval_Firing_Practice_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where Naval forces (for example: vessels or aircraft) conduct firing and/or munition exercises.

Subcode.Label: Naval_Operations_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where Naval forces conduct operations.

Subcode.Label: Measured_Dist_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A course whose length has been accurately measured and is used in conjunction with ranges ashore. It is used by vessels to calibrate logs, engine revolution counters, etc., and determine speed.

Subcode.Label: Theodolite_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Lines of known bearing from fixed geographic locations. Used to determine accurate positions of a vessel on certain test ranges.

Subcode.Label: Range_Centerline
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A surveyed reference track marking the center of a test range. Vessels undergoing testing must maintain position along this track.

Subcode.Label: Radar_Ref_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line shown on a chart in proximity to a shipping route, along which ships are guided by a traffic control center located in a radar station. (See also BC032)

Subcode.Label: Route-Maritime
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A track or lane established for the safe passage of ships. (Retired; complex features no longer needed).

Subcode.Label: Route-Deep_Water
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Complex feature with possible components: FC165 and RTT098, FC165 and RTT099, BC099, BC098. (Retired; complex features no longer needed).

Subcode.Label: Defined_Water
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Complex feature with possible components: FC165 and RTT008, FC165 and RTT012, AT060 and STA032, AT050 and STA033, GA055, BB011, BC099, BC098, and BB007.

Subcode.Label: Route-Canal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A navigable channel in lakes or other waterways. (Superseded by Channel (BH191); use attribution if the type of waterbody is required).

Subcode.Label: Safety_Fairway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A route established for the safe passage of vessels through offshore oil and gas fields and minefields.

Subcode.Label: Swept_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area that has been determined to be clear of navigational dangers to a specified depth.

Subcode.Label: Side_Scan_Sonar_Coverage
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of horizontal coverage recorded by side scan SONAR survey.

Subcode.Label: Mine_Counter_Measure_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where Mine Counter Measure operations have taken place.

Subcode.Label: Airspace
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Designated airspace within which some or all aircraft may be subjected to air traffic control.

Subcode.Label: ATS_Segment
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A portion of an Air Traffic Service (ATS) Route identified by two electronic NAVAIDS at the extremities and/or reporting points.

Subcode.Label: Spec_Use_Airspace
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Airspace of defined dimension identified by area on Earth's surface where activities must be confined because of their nature and/or where limitations may be imposed on aircraft operations not associated with those activities.

Subcode.Label: Airspace_Bndry_Seg
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Single segment of an Airspace (GA005).

Subcode.Label: Spec_Airspace_Seg
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Single segment of a Special Use Airspace (GA015).

Subcode.Label: Off_Route_Bearing
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Captures the Off Route Radials/Bearings (directions and distance from a NAVAID to a Waypoint).

Subcode.Label: Lead_Radial
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A radial or bearing which provides at least 2 miles of lead to assist in turning onto the intermediate portion of an instrument approach when the angle of intercept is greater than 90 degrees.

Subcode.Label: NAVAIDS
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Any visual or electronic device which provides point-to-point guidance information or position data.

Subcode.Label: Route
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A specific route designated for channeling the flow or traffic as necessary for the provision of air traffic services.

Subcode.Label: Terminal_Route
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Definition of route segments, action points, and various approach minimum altitudes and distances from the end of landing runway as functions of aircraft type and instrument approach procedures.

Subcode.Label: ILS_Component
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Navigation Components which are essential to the establishment and execution of a precision approach based on the Instrument Landing System (ILS).

Subcode.Label: ILS_Terminal_Seg
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A specific terminal route/segment designated for channeling the flow of traffic via Instrument Landing System (ILS) terminal procedures.

Subcode.Label: Waypoint
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A predetermined geographical position, used for route instrument approach definition or progress reporting purposes or to change frequency etc.

Subcode.Label: Air_Warning_Light
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A light or lights marking an obstacle which constitutes a danger to air navigation.

Subcode.Label: Primary_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An imaginary surface, longitudinally centered on each runway, at a length of the runway length plus 1000 feet on each end, and a width of 2,000 feet.

Subcode.Label: Apprch_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An inclined plane, symmetrical about the runway centerline, beginning 200 feet outboard of the runway end point, at the height of the runway end point and extending for 42332 feet (7nm - 200 feet of primary surface). The slope of the approach clearance surface is 50 to 1 along the runway centerline extended until it reaches a height of 500 feet above the height of the lowest runway end on the airport. It then continues horizontally at this height to a point 42532 feet (7nm) from the end of the runway. The width of this surface at the runway end is the same as the primary surface, it flares uniformly, and the width at 42,532 feet is 13,899 feet.

Subcode.Label: Apprch_Trans_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: This surface connects the side of the runway primary and approach surfaces to the inner horizontal surface. The surface extends outward, perpendicular to the centerline of each runway, from the edges of the primary surface, at a slope of 7:1 to a width of 1050 feet and a height of 150 feet above the lowest runway end.

Subcode.Label: Inner_Hor_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The inner horizontal surface for each runway is defined by two half circles centered on the runway ends and joined by tangents. The radii of the half circles are 7500 feet and the tangents are parallel to the runway centerline at a distance of 7500 feet. The surface is a constant 150 feet above the lowest runway end.

Subcode.Label: Conical_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A surface extending from the periphery of the inner horizontal surface outward and upward at a slope of 20:1 for a horizontal distance of 7000 feet to a height of 500 feet above the lowest runway end.

Subcode.Label: Outer_Hor_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A plane, located 500 feet above the lowest runway end, extending outward from the outer periphery of the conical surface for a horizontal distance of 28032 feet.

Subcode.Label: Hor_Trans_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: This surface connects the side of the approach surface to the conical and outer horizontal surface. The surface extends outward, perpendicular to the extended runway centerline from the edges of the approach surface, at a 7:1 slope. The slope of the 7:1 surface is referenced to the runway centerline.

Subcode.Label: Aerodrome_Associated_Strip
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A linear terrain feature (for example: a drag strip) that falls within the coverage of the airport sketch.

Subcode.Label: Airport
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of land set aside for the take-off, landing and/or accommodation of aircraft. (Revised concept but same code that excludes water-based facilities).

Subcode.Label: Airfield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A land aerodrome with limited facilities.

Subcode.Label: Airport_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tract of land used for landing, take-off, and movement of aircraft not including associated buildings, runways and other facilities.

Subcode.Label: Airport_Lighting
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Lights used to: define and outline perimeters, runways, taxiways, etc.; guide aircraft while on the ground, and to provide guidance to aircraft on approach for landing.

Subcode.Label: Apron
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A defined paved or hard-packed area at an airport or heliport intended for aircraft parking.

Subcode.Label: Arresting_Gear
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Devices such as cables or barriers that can be used to stop an aircraft immediately upon landing.

Subcode.Label: Blast_Barrier
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A barrier used to divert or dissipate jet or propeller blast.

Subcode.Label: Helo_Landing_Pad
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An improved area used for take-off, and landing, by helicopters and other vertical take-off and landing aircraft.

Subcode.Label: Heliport
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An improved area used for take-off and landing of helicopters. (Revised concept but same code that is restricted to helicoptors (VTOL are much heavier and require stronger landing surfaces)

Subcode.Label: Launch_Pad
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A designated area or structure from which a rocket or missile is launched.

Subcode.Label: Overrun_or_Stopway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area beyond the take-off runway designated as able to support an airplane during an aborted take-off.

Subcode.Label: Touchdown_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The first 3000 feet of the runway beginning at the threshold. The threshold is the beginning of that portion of the runway available for landing .

Subcode.Label: Revetment
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A barricade which protects an aircraft, equipment, or facilities from hostile action.

Subcode.Label: Runway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A defined area, usually rectangular, used for the conventional landing and take-off of aircraft. (Excludes GB045)

Subcode.Label: Runway_Endpoint
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The points located on the centerline at the ends of the runway.

Subcode.Label: Shoulder
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Adjacent area along either side of a road or runway not normally used by vehicles or aircraft, but provided as an allowable margin in case of emergency situations.

Subcode.Label: Point_Abeam
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The point on a line that is nearest to an off line point. For example, a point on the runway centerline is abeam the Glide Slope Antenna when the distance from the centerline point to the antenna is a minimum.

Subcode.Label: Airfield_Elev_Pt
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The highest point of an airport's usable runways measured in feet from the geoid (orthometric height).

Subcode.Label: Rwy_Radar_Reflector
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A device, normally placed near the threshold of a runway, used for reflecting radar signals.

Subcode.Label: Seaplane_Base
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An installation supporting aircraft capable of taking off and landing on water.

Subcode.Label: Seaplane_Ldg_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A designated portion of water outlined by visual surface markings, used by seaplanes to land and take off.

Subcode.Label: Taxiway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A prepared surface providing access to/from runways and the aircraft parking area, terminal area, or service area, etc.

Subcode.Label: Wind_Sock
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A visual device used to provide wind information.

Subcode.Label: Displaced_Threshold
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The designated beginning of the portion of the runway usable for landing. This is located at a point on the runway other than the designated beginning of the runway. In addition, the feature typically exists at each end of the runway.

Subcode.Label: Decontamination_Pad
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A designated area where a Nuclear, Biological, or Chemical (NBC) contaminated aircraft, checked at landing, is sent to be decontaminated by special teams.

Subcode.Label: INS_Alignment_Pad
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A designated area where the automated navigation instruments of aircraft are reset before taking off.

Subcode.Label: Air_Obstruction
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An existing object of natural growth, or terrain at a fixed location within prescribed area with a reference to which vertical clearance is or must be provided during flight operations. (Revised concept but same code that allows for either natural or man-made; where needed distinguish using Attribute: Man-made).

Subcode.Label: Misc_Obstruction
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An object at a fixed location with reference to which vertical clearance is or must be provided during flight operations. (Superseded by Air Obstruction (GB220) which has been revised to include man-made obstructions.)

Subcode.Label: Low_Air_Maneuver_Pylon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A vertical structure that is used to mark turns and/or provide obstacles around which aircraft may perform low level aerobatic manoeuvres (for example: during racing or training).

Subcode.Label: Aircraft_Hangar
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building for housing aircraft.

Subcode.Label: Hardened_Aircraft_Shelter
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A hardened structure built above or partially above ground that encloses aircraft to provide protection from enemy attack.

Subcode.Label: Runway_Distance_Sign
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A sign installed on airfields in accordance to Advisory Circular 150/5340-1J and FAA Aeronautical Information Manual.

Subcode.Label: Runway_Element
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A part of a runway (as defined by DO-272B). A Runway_Element is delimited by the outer edge of the white runway edge painting or surface edge if no marking is present, excluding runway shoulders.

Subcode.Label: Runway_Intersection
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The intersecting area shared by two or more runways (as defined by DO-272B). The Runway_Intersection is delimited by the outge of the white runway edge painting or surface edge if no marking is present, excluding runway shoulders.

Subcode.Label: Runway_Threshold
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The beginning of that portion of the runway that is available for landing (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Runway_Marking
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A symbol or group of symbols displayed on the surface of the runway in order to convey aeronautical information (as defined by DO-272B). Includines runway designation marking, runway centerline marking, threshold marking, traverse stripes, touchdown zone marking and runway side strip marking.

Subcode.Label: Painted_Centerline
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A continuous line captured along the painted line in the center of a runway connecting the two threshold (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: LAHSO_Location
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Location of marking used for Land and Hold Short Operations (as defined by DO-272B). These runway operations include landing and holding short of an intersecting runway, an intersecting taxiway, or on some other designated point on a runway other than an intersecting runway or taxiway.

Subcode.Label: Arresting_Gear_Location
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Location of the arresting gear cable across the runway (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Runway_Shoulder
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area adjacent to the edge of a runway pavement so prepared as to provide a transition between the pavement and the adjacent surface (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Stopway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A defined rectangular area on the ground at the end of takeoff run available prepared as a suitable area in which an aircraft can be stopped in the case of an abandoned takeoff (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Runway_Displaced_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: That portion of a runway between the beginning of the runway and the displaced threshold (as defined by DO-272B). Does not include runway shoulders.

Subcode.Label: Blastpad
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Specially prepared surface placed adjacent to the end of a runway to eliminate the erosive effect of the high wind forces produced by airplanes at the beginning of their taqkeoff roll (as defined by DO-272B). The area is usually covered in chevrons. Blastpads may not be used for taxiing, landing or takeoff.

Subcode.Label: Runway_Exit_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A guidance line painted on the runway exit (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Helipad_FATO
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Helipad Final Approach and Take-off Area - the beginning of that portion of the helipad that is available for landing (as defined by DO-272B). The outer edge of the white FATO-marking should be used to represent the FATO

Subcode.Label: Helipad_TLOF
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Helipad Touchdown/Lift-off Area - a load bearing area on which a helicopter may touchdown or liftoff (as defined by DO-272B). The outer edge of the white TLOF-marking should be used to represent the TLOF

Subcode.Label: Helipad_Threshold
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The threshold of a helipad (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Taxiway_Element
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A part of a taxiway. A Taxiway_Element is delimited by the outer side of the taxiway edge marking (as defined by DO-272B). Includes taxiways, apron taxiways, rapid exit taxiways, and aircraft stand taxilane surfaces.

Subcode.Label: Taxiway_Shoulder
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area adjacent to the edge of a taxiway pavement so prepared as to provide a transition between the pavement and the adjacent surface (as defined by DO-272B). Should exclude the taxiway edge marking

Subcode.Label: Taxiway_Guidance_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A guidance line painted on a taxiway (as defined by DO-272B). Excludes exit lines and stand guidance taxilines.

Subcode.Label: Taxiway_Intxn_Marking
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A taxiway intersection marking painted across a taxiway (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Taxiway_Holding_Position
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A taxiway holding position painted across a taxiway (as defined by DO-272B); it is located at the outer edge of the painted ground marking away from the corresponding runway.

Subcode.Label: Frequency_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The designated part of a surface movement area where a specific frequency is required by air traffic control or ground control (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Apron_Element
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The remaining parts of a defined apron area that are not covered by Parking Stand Area features or Taxiway Element features (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Stand_Guidance_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A guidance line on a designated area on an apron intended to be used for parking an aircraft (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Parking_Stand_Location
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The location of an aircraft stand (as defined by DO-272B). There may be multiple Parking_Stand_Locations within one Parking_Stand_Area.

Subcode.Label: Parking_Stand_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A designated area on an apron intended to be used for parking an aircraft (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Deicing_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area comprising an inner area for the parking of an airplane to receive de-icing treatment and an outer area for the maneuvering of two or more mobile de-icing equipment (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Service_Road
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The part of an aerodrome surface used by service vehicles (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Aerodrome_Ref_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The designated geographical location of an aerodrome (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Poly_Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The footprint of a structure (typically building) whose maximum height exceeds the defined vertical limit as defined in section 3.11 of the DO-272B specification and that is located within an area that extends from the edges of the runways to 90 m from the runway centerline.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Point_Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The location of a structure (typically tower) whose maximum height exceeds the defined vertical limit as defined in section 3.11 of the DO-272B specification and that is located within an area that extends from the edges of the runways to 90 m from the runway centerline.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Line_Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The centerline of a structure (typically powerline) whose maximum height exceeds the defined vertical limit as defined in section 3.11 of the DO-272B specification and that is located within an area that extends from the edges of the runways to 90 m from the runway centerline.

Subcode.Label: Construction_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A part of a movement area (e.g. a runway, taxiway, apron, parking stand, de-icing area) under construction (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Water
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A water body close to the movement zone (as defined by DO-272B)

Subcode.Label: Hotspot
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A location on an aerodrome movement area with a history or potential risk of collision or runway incursion and where heightened attention by pilots/drivers is necessary (as defined by DO-272B)

Subcode.Label: Aerodrome_Surface_Light
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Individual airport surface lights that are located within a buffer 90 m from runway centerline and 50 m from edge of aircraft movement zone (as defined by DO-272B).

Subcode.Label: Map_Boundary
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line which encloses all water, streets, parcels and buildings. (Retired; this cartographic object appears to no longer be in use (if ever)

Subcode.Label: Parcel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Land use and/or land property.

Subcode.Label: Tract
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region of land with definite boundaries, especially one intended for development.

Subcode.Label: Cadastral_Const
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Constructions with unique characteristics. (Retired; Ill-defined and apparently not in use)

Subcode.Label: Cadastral_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A reference point used for a cadastral map orientation.

Subcode.Label: Fiducial_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Used for topographic survey. (Retired; Ill-defined and apparently not in use)

Subcode.Label: Map_Sheet
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Contains drawing frames and map parameters. (Retired; Ill-defined and apparently not in use)

Subcode.Label: Misc
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Contains topographical details and other information. (Retired; Ill-defined and apparently not in use)

Subcode.Label: Map_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Contains auxiliary information about each map. (Retired; Ill-defined and apparently not in use)

Subcode.Label: Agricultural_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A global land-use zone based on a predominant form and type of plant cultivation.

Subcode.Label: Time_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Any of the 24 longitudinal regions of the Earth, each occupying 15 arc degrees and having a mean solar time one hour greater than that of the neighboring region to its west.

Subcode.Label: Monument
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A recognizable feature in the terrain that is subject to defined protective rules (for example: world cultural heritage).

Subcode.Label: Land_Reclamation_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of new land that has been reclaimed from an area previously covered by water.

Subcode.Label: Transport_Link
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A route that links two locations and is served by regularly scheduled transport.

Subcode.Label: Solid_Rock
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area consisting of an aggregate of one or more minerals and/or solid organic material.

Subcode.Label: Erosion_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the land where removal processes have caused an areal degradation of soil particles (for example: erosion by the action of the wind) or to a linear degradation with deep erosion of different grades (for example: erosion by the action of moving water).

Subcode.Label: Geologic_Mass_Movement
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area within which dislodgment and downslope transport of soil and/or bedrock under the influence of gravity has occurred.

Subcode.Label: Geologic_Structure_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A line along which large scale, linear tectonic manifestations have occurred.

Subcode.Label: Soil_Salinization_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area within which the upper soil horizons have become enriched in salts to a sufficient degree to result in loss in agricultural productivity.

Subcode.Label: Mineral_Occurrence_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area, place, site or deposit, of which little may be known, except that specific minerals or rocks, that are considered to be valuable or that are of scientific or technical interest, have been identified and recorded.

Subcode.Label: Hydrogeologic_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of similar hydrogeologic properties and conditions of groundwater.

Subcode.Label: Epicentre
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The point on the surface of the Earth that is directly above the focus of an earthquake.

Subcode.Label: Earthquake_Damage_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that has been damaged by an earthquake.

Subcode.Label: Geologic_Mapping_Unit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its tectono-, litho-, bio-, and/or chronostratigraphic properties.

Subcode.Label: Hydrogeologic_Mapping_Unit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its substratum (bodies of soil, rock and unconsolidated rocks) and its groundwater related properties.

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Relief
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth characterized by a common surface form or set of related surface forms.

Subcode.Label: Vegetation_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A global zone based on a predominant plant community.

Subcode.Label: Tree_Limit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The point in altitude and/or latitude beyond which trees can no longer grow.

Subcode.Label: Settlement_Limit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A boundary or limit beyond which human settlement is either not possible or not appropriate for climatic or topographic reasons.

Subcode.Label: Cultivation_Limit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A boundary or limit beyond which plant cultivation is not possible.

Subcode.Label: Drainage_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the terrain sharing a common outflow for surface water runoff.

Subcode.Label: Desertification_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the terrain that is subject to a persisting change of landscape towards that of desert that is typically caused by agriculture together with over-use of the ecosystem.

Subcode.Label: Dry_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the terrain where the rate of evaporation is exceeds the rate of precipitation.

Subcode.Label: Aggradation_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area within which lakes are disappearing due to either the diversion of inflowing water or the desposition of (typically fine) sediments and plant colonization.

Subcode.Label: Ecological_Crisis_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area subject to extreme incidents that stress and may irreversibly injure the environment

Subcode.Label: Contaminated_Site
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area within which refuse has been dumped on land or sunk (legally or illegally) in the sea and has resulted in environmental endangerment.

Subcode.Label: Infection_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area within which a fast-spreading infectious disease occurs.

Subcode.Label: Hazardous_Biome_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth where animals and/or plants may endanger or kill human life directly (by attack) or indirectly (by poison).

Subcode.Label: Precipitation_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its level of precipitation.

Subcode.Label: Atmospheric_Humidity_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its level of atmospheric humidity.

Subcode.Label: Solar_Irradiance_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its solar irradiance.

Subcode.Label: Frost_and_or_Snow_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its annual period of frost and/or snow.

Subcode.Label: Fog_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its annual period of fog.

Subcode.Label: Global_Wind_Belt
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A major area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its permanent wind circulation.

Subcode.Label: Regional_Wind_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A regional area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its wind circulation.

Subcode.Label: Atmospheric_Pressure_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its atmospheric pressure.

Subcode.Label: Extreme_Wind_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area of the surface of the Earth that shares a common characterization of its wind circulation as having more or less regular (periodic, partly episodic) occurring strong winds with speeds more than 75 kilometres per hour (9 Beaufort or greater).

Subcode.Label: Ocean_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: One of the three large regions of the world-wide ocean, each with associated sub- and marginal areas and subject to an independent flow-regime.

Subcode.Label: Common_Open_Water
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area containing any surface water that is flowing or free standing such as lakes, rivers, oceans, reservoirs, etc.

Subcode.Label: Disturbed_Soil
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area that has been so disturbed by human activity that no single soil type can be accurately identified. These areas may include built-up areas, strip mines, landfills, railroad yards, etc.

Subcode.Label: Exposed_Bedrock
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Areas that contain no or little soil (less than 10%) containing bare rock or other extrusive material such as lava.

Subcode.Label: Permanent_Snowfield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area permanently covered by snow or ice that covers a land mass, such as glaciers and snowfields.

Subcode.Label: Slope_Polygon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A region where the terrain slope is within a set range of values.

Subcode.Label: Covered_Drainage
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A natural watercourse or man-made waterway that is covered preventing its observation or

Subcode.Label: Seismic_Activity_Area
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where earthquakes or other seismic events routinely occur.

Subcode.Label: Military_Base
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A center of operations for a military organization.

Subcode.Label: Subway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An underground, metropolitan electric railway or the tunnel through which it travels. (Revised concept but same code that is focused on the railway alone).

Subcode.Label: Port_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A building or section of building that is established to serve a particular purpose for water

Subcode.Label: Aperture
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An opening and/or hole in an OBJECT, especially a STRUCTURE; an aperture.

Subcode.Label: Component
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBJECT that is a constituent part of another (aggregate) OBJECT but, by itself, does not fulfill the function of the aggregate; a component.

Subcode.Label: Datum
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBJECT used as a reference for defining spatial aspects of other OBJECTs; a datum.

Subcode.Label: Furniture
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Movable, functional OBJECTs, whether useful or ornamental, usually found in a BUILDING; furniture [SOED, "furniture", 6].

Subcode.Label: Man_Made_Object
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBJECT made by HUMANs; a man-made object.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Object
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBJECT relating to or characteristic of VESSELs, shipping, sailors, or navigation on a WATERBODY; a marine object [SOED, "marine", B.2].

Subcode.Label: Mesh
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An abstract OBJECT consisting of three related NON_EMPTY_SETs: a MESH_NODE_SET, a MESH_EDGE_SET, and a MESH_FACE_SET; a mesh.

Subcode.Label: Non_Empty_Set
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SET with at least one member; a non-empty set.

Subcode.Label: Object
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A person, place, thing, or concept; an object.

Subcode.Label: Object_Set
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of OBJECTs.

Subcode.Label: Related_Object_Set
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of related OBJECTs.

Subcode.Label: Set
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A possibly empty collection of distinct OBJECTs; a set.

Subcode.Label: System
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of OBJECTs arranged or organized for a special purpose and functioning together as a whole; a system [SOED, "system", 3].

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Surface_Object
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBJECT located on the TERRAIN. EXAMPLE Man-made STRUCTURE.

Subcode.Label: Time_Analysis_Base_Set
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of OBJECTs with EDCS Attributes that are analyzed at a common base time.

Subcode.Label: Time_Forecast_Tau_Set
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of OBJECTs with EDCS Attributes that are forecasted at a time offset from a TIME_ANALYSIS_BASE_SET time.

Subcode.Label: Flagpole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A POLE on which a flag is raised; a flagstaff or flagpole.

Subcode.Label: Haystack
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A regular pile of hay built in the open air; a haystack.

Subcode.Label: Mixed_Urban_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION containing STRUCTUREs in combination with undeveloped and/or agricultural TRACTs; a mixed urban region.

Subcode.Label: Aperture_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A generic APERTURE

Subcode.Label: Breach_Hole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A rough opening in a WALL for HUMAN entrance or egress, usually created by hand emplaced demolition charges or projectile munitions, typically about 60 centimetres in diameter; a wall breach.

Subcode.Label: Building_Component_Entrance_Exit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An ENTRANCE_AND_OR_EXIT between BUILDING_COMPONENTs, such as a doorway or a passage to a STAIR landing.

Subcode.Label: Door
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A hinged or sliding BARRIER to part of a STRUCTURE or VEHICLE, constructed of wood or other MATERIAL; a door.

Subcode.Label: Entrance_or_Exit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A GATE, HALLWAY or DOOR used for ingress or egress or both.

Subcode.Label: Wall_Opening_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An uncovered opening in an WALL to support the passage of MATERIALs or visibility into an adjoining ROOM, including the space above a partial-height WALL.

Subcode.Label: Exterior_Wall_Opening
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An uncovered opening in an EXTERIOR_WALL to support the passage of MATERIALs or visibility into an adjoining ROOM, including the space above a partial-height WALL.

Subcode.Label: Interior_Wall_Opening
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An uncovered opening in an INTERIOR_WALL to support the passage of MATERIALs or visibility into an adjoining ROOM, including the space above a partial-height WALL.

Subcode.Label: Partition_Opening_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An opening in a partition, e.g., BREACH_HOLE, DOOR, WINDOW or TRAP_DOOR.

Subcode.Label: Horizontal_Partition_Opening
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An opening in a horizontal partition, e.g., SKYLIGHT or TRAP_DOOR.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Partition_Opening
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An opening in a vertical partition, e.g., WINDOW, DOOR.

Subcode.Label: Trap_Door
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DOOR flush with the surface, in a FLOOR, ROOF, or CEILING; a trap door.

Subcode.Label: Wall_Loophole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small opening in a WALL for observation, weapons firing, or to allow hand grenades to be thrown into a defended STRUCTURE, typically about 20 centimetres in diameter; a loophole.

Subcode.Label: Window
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An opening in a WALL or the side of a BUILDING, VEHICLE, or other STRUCTURE, to admit light or AIR or both, and to afford a view of what is outside or inside; a window.

Subcode.Label: Ventilation_Opening
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An opening, generally covered, into a VENTILATION_DUCT or VENTILATION_SHAFT, which may be large enough to admit a HUMAN.

Subcode.Label: Room_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A generic ROOM

Subcode.Label: Anteroom
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A ROOM before, or forming an entrance to, another; an anteroom, foyer or entrance hall.

Subcode.Label: Atrium
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A usually skylit central court in a BUILDING rising through several FLOOR_LEVELs and surrounded by galleries at each FLOOR_LEVEL with ROOMS opening off; an atrium.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Room_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interior or exterior enclosure for human occupancy or movement, e.g., ROOM, CATWALK or EXTERIOR_HALLWAY.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Room_Exterior
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An exterior enclosure for human occupancy or movement, e.g. ROOM, COURTYARD or EXTERIOR_HALLWAY.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Room_Interior
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interior room.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Shaft
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A vertical enclosure in a building which generally spans multiple levels, e.g., ELEVATOR_SHAFT, VENTILATION_SHAFT

Subcode.Label: Balcony
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A platform projecting from the WALL of a BUILDING or ROOM, supported by pillars or brackets, and enclosed by a balustrade; a balcony or deck.

Subcode.Label: Catwalk
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A suspended narrow footway or platform; a catwalk.

Subcode.Label: Closet
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small ROOM, belonging to or communicating with a larger ROOM; a closet.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Duct
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A ventilation or other duct which may support human movement

Subcode.Label: Courtyard
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open area surrounded by WALLs or BUILDINGs within the precincts of a large BUILDING, CASTLE, or BUILT_UP_REGION; a courtyard.

Subcode.Label: Elevator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT consisting of a platform, often enclosed, which is raised and lowered in a vertical shaft to transport PERSONNEL, EQUIPMENT or MATERIALs; an elevator.

Subcode.Label: Elevator_Shaft
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A vertical passageway in a BUILDING used for ELEVATORs; an elevator shaft.

Subcode.Label: Escalator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT consisting of moving STAIR made on the endless-chain principle, so that the steps ascend or descend continuously, for carrying PERSONNEL up or down; an escalator.

Subcode.Label: Exterior_Hallway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A HALLWAY along the exterior of a BUILDING, often appearing as a long BALCONY.

Subcode.Label: Fire_Escape
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An exterior STRUCTURE or DEVICE, such as an outside STAIR attached to a BUILDING, erected for emergency exit in the event of fire; a fire escape.

Subcode.Label: Hallway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An entrance-hall or passage serving as a ROUTE to various ROOMs in a BUILDING; a hallway or corridor.

Subcode.Label: Pulpit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A raised STRUCTURE consisting of an enclosed platform from which the preacher in a CHURCH or CHAPEL delivers the sermon; a pulpit.

Subcode.Label: Ramp
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An inclined plane, usually man-made, for moving between two levels; a ramp.

Subcode.Label: Stair
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An ascending series or flight of steps leading from one FLOOR_LEVEL to another; a stair.

Subcode.Label: Ventilation_Duct
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A predominantly horizontal duct for the admission of a proper supply of fresh or temperature controlled air, especially to a ROOM, BUILDING or other place where the AIR readily becomes stagnant or in need of temperature control; a ventilation duct.

Subcode.Label: Ventilation_Shaft
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A vertical or slightly inclined passageway in a BUILDING used for heating or ventilation; a ventilation shaft.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Passage_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An enclosure that provides passage between levels in a building, e.g., STAIR, ELEVATOR_SHAFT or FIRE_ESCAPE.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Passage_Exterior
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An exterior enclosure that provides passage between levels in a building, e.g., STAIR, ELEVATOR_SHAFT.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Passage_Interior
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An interior enclosure that provides passage between levels in a building, e.g., STAIR, ELEVATOR_SHAFT.

Subcode.Label: Stair_Set
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SET of STAIRs connecting three or more FLOOR_LEVELs in an uninterrupted sequence.

Subcode.Label: Section_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large convex hull portion of a 3D model physically separating the model into manageable chunks. A 3D model is composed of at least one section.

Subcode.Label: Fixture_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A generic FIXTURE

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Content_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Fixed or mobile items contained in a compartment, e.g., FURNITURE or HEAT_RADIATOR.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Content_Fixed
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Fixed items contained in a compartment, e.g., HEAT_RADIATOR.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Content_Mobile
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Mobile items contained in a compartment, e.g., FURNITURE.

Subcode.Label: Control_Panel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A panel on which are mounted switches, dials, and other mechanisms for the remote control or operation of electrical or other EQUIPMENT; a control panel.

Subcode.Label: Furnace
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE in which energy in a nonthermal form is converted to heat.

Subcode.Label: Furniture
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Movable articles, whether useful or ornamental, in a BUILDING; furniture.

Subcode.Label: Heat_Radiator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT consisting of a tank or compact array of PIPEs, having a large surface area, which is heated usually by circulating steam or hot water and gives off warmth also by convection; a heat radiator.

Subcode.Label: Floor_Level_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SET of ROOMs and STAIR landings in a BUILDING that are on the same or nearly the same level; a floor level or storey.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Layer_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A set of rooms in a building at nearly the same level, e.g., ATTIC, BASEMENT or FLOOR_LEVEL.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Layer_Inhabitable
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A compartment layer which is suitable for habitation, e.g., ATTIC, BASEMENT, FLOOR_LEVEL.

Subcode.Label: Compartment_Layer_Uninhabitable
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A compartment layer which is not suitable for habitation, e.g., FLOOR_CRAWL_SPACE, ROOF_ASSEMBLY.

Subcode.Label: Attic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A space or room on the uppermost FLOOR_LEVEL of a BUILDING, formed either partially or wholly within the ROOF; an attic or garret.

Subcode.Label: Basement
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The lowest FLOOR_LEVEL (not a cellar) of a BUILDING, especially when sunk below the TERRAIN; a basement.

Subcode.Label: Crawl_Space_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Aspace in a BUILDING providing access to ducts and of sufficient height for crawling; a ceiling or floor crawl space.

Subcode.Label: Ceiling_Crawl_Space
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An above-ceiling space in a BUILDING providing access to ducts and of sufficient height for crawling; a ceiling crawl space.

Subcode.Label: Floor_Crawl_Space
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An underfloor space in a BUILDING providing access to VENTILATION_DUCTs and of sufficient height for crawling; a crawl space.

Subcode.Label: Mezzanine
Subcode.Concept_Definition: In a BUILDING, a low FLOOR_LEVEL between two higher ones, especially a low FLOOR_LEVEL between the ground FLOOR_LEVEL and the FLOOR_LEVEL above, occasionally between the ground FLOOR_LEVEL and the BASEMENT; a mezzanine.

Subcode.Label: Roof_Assembly
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A ROOF and its structural support; a roof assembly.

Subcode.Label: Ceiling
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The overhead inside lining of a ROOM; a ceiling.

Subcode.Label: Floor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The layer of MATERIAL, such as boards, brick, or stone, in ROOM, on which people tread; a floor.

Subcode.Label: Partition_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A horizontal or vertical structure that separates enclosures in a building, e.g., FLOOR or INTERIOR_WALL.

Subcode.Label: Horizontal_Partition
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A horizontal partition in a building, e.g., FLOOR or CEILING.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Partition
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A vertical partition, e.g., INTERIOR_WALL, EXTERIOR_WALL.

Subcode.Label: Ventilation_Duct_Wall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The WALLs or casing of a VENTILATION_DUCT.

Subcode.Label: Wall_Generic
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An exterior or interior WALL

Subcode.Label: Exterior_Wall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WALL forming an exterior of a STRUCTURE, connecting the foundation and ROOF (if present).

Subcode.Label: Interior_Wall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WALL in a BUILDING separating two ROOMs from each other; an interior wall.

Subcode.Label: Boundary_Component
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A COMPONENT of a BOUNDARY.

Subcode.Label: Change_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LINE within a REGION indicating where the properties of the REGION change significantly; a change line.

Subcode.Label: Data_Quality_Boundary
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BOUNDARY between two DATA_QUALITY_REGIONs.

Subcode.Label: Acoustic_Transducer
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DEVICE to transform acoustic energy to and/or from electrical energy; an acoustic transducer.

Subcode.Label: Anemometer
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WIND_INDICATOR designed to measure total WIND_SPEED or the SPEED of one or more linear (vector) components of the WIND; an anemometer.

Subcode.Label: Automated_Teller_Machine
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DEVICE that provides money and/or performs banking services when a special card is inserted and a password is typed in; an automated teller machine [SOED, "teller", II.2.a; "automated teller machine"].

Subcode.Label: Control_Panel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A panel on which are mounted switches, dials, and/or other mechanisms for the remote control and/or operation of EQUIPMENT (for example: electrical EQUIPMENT).

Subcode.Label: Device
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An OBJECT designed for a particular function or adapted for a particular purpose, especially a (simple) mechanical contrivance; a device [SOED, "device", 3].

Subcode.Label: Dragline
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Excavating EQUIPMENT consisting of a steel scoop that swings on CHAINs from a movable jib; the scoop is cast into the MATERIAL to be excavated and dragged back to the jib where it is lifted and dumped; a dragline.

Subcode.Label: Equipment
Subcode.Concept_Definition: OBJECTs used and/or required for a particular purpose; equipment [SOED, "equipment", 2] or apparatus.

Subcode.Label: Equipment_Component
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A COMPONENT of an item of EQUIPMENT.

Subcode.Label: Escalator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT consisting of a moving STAIR made on the endless-chain principle, so that the steps ascend or descend continuously, for carrying HUMANs up or down; an escalator [SOED, "escalator"].

Subcode.Label: Explosive_Charge
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An explosive DEVICE that may be detonated to either damage or destroy STRUCTUREs or to move ROCK, SOIL, and/or other MATERIALs; an explosive charge.

Subcode.Label: Explosive_Land_Mine
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An EXPLOSIVE_MINE used in land warfare.

Subcode.Label: Explosive_Mine
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An explosive DEVICE located on or below a PLANETARY_SURFACE, usually emplaced for military purposes; an explosive mine [SOED, "land-mine", a].

Subcode.Label: Fire_Escape
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An exterior STRUCTURE or DEVICE erected for emergency exit in the event of fire; a fire-escape [AHD, "fire escape"]. EXAMPLE An outside STAIR that is attached to a BUILDING.

Subcode.Label: Food_Oven
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT consisting of a chamber or enclosed compartment for heating, baking, or roasting food; an oven or stove [AHD, "oven"].

Subcode.Label: Heat_Radiator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT consisting of a STORAGE_TANK and/or compact array of PIPEs that: has a large surface AREA; is heated, usually by circulating steam or hot WATER; and gives off warmth by radiation and convection; a heat radiator [SOED, "radiator", 2].

Subcode.Label: Lift
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT consisting of a platform, which is often enclosed, that is raised and lowered in a vertical shaft to transport HUMANs, EQUIPMENT, or MATERIALs; a lift or an elevator (US) [AHD, "elevator", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Marine_Aid_To_Navigation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An AID_TO_NAVIGATION (for example: a BEACON and/or a BUOY) intended to support marine operations.

Subcode.Label: Munition
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DEVICE charged with: explosives; propellant; pyrotechnics; initiating composition; or nuclear, chemical, or biological MATERIAL for use in military operations (for example: demolitions); a munition.

Subcode.Label: Refuse_Bin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A CONTAINER that: is of several cubic metres capacity; is used for the collection of refuse; and is designed to be hoisted and emptied into a specially equipped TRUCK or, occasionally, hauled away; a refuse bin.

Subcode.Label: Shovel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT for EXCAVATION that moves MATERIALs by a scooping action; a shovel.

Subcode.Label: Supplies_And_Expendables
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of EQUIPMENT and/or MATERIAL that may be consumed or discarded after use; supplies and expendables.

Subcode.Label: Underwater_Communication_Device
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DEVICE located in a WATERBODY and used to provide two-way communication; an underwater communication device. EXAMPLE ACOUSTIC_TRANSDUCER.

Subcode.Label: Wind_Vane
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A visual DEVICE used to indicate or measure WIND_DIRECTION; a wind vane.

Subcode.Label: Container
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DEVICE designed to contain MATERIALs; a container [SOED, "container"].

Subcode.Label: Railway_Signal_Box
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Automated EQUIPMENT from which signals are sent to control the movements of TRAINs; a signal box or signal tower.

Subcode.Label: Breakwater
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE that protects a WATERBODY_REGION (for example: a SHORE, a HARBOUR, an ANCHORAGE, and/or a WATERBODY_SHELTER_BASIN) from WATER_WAVEs by preventing them from reaching the protected REGION or reducing their magnitude; a breakwater.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Hydrography Network Lineal Figure Pt, Hydrography Network Areal Figure Pt

Subcode.Label: Dyke
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An artificial EMBANKMENT to contain WATER; a dyke.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Hydrography Network Lineal Figure Pt, Hydrography Network Areal Figure Pt

Subcode.Label: Lock_Gate
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A pair of massive, hinged DOORs at the end of a LOCK_BASIN; a lock gate.

Subcode.Label: Non_Submarine_Contact
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Any OBJECT (for example: a MARINE_WRECK) on a WATERBODY_FLOOR that could be mistakenly identified as an operable SUBMERSIBLE_VESSEL when detected with acoustic or magnetic sensors; a non-submarine contact.

Subcode.Label: Shoreline_Construction
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A fixed (not afloat) artificial STRUCTURE attached to a SHORE and normally used for berthing and protection of VESSELs; a shoreline construction.

Subcode.Label: Tide_Lock
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A HYDROGRAPHIC_LOCK situated between a WATERBODY_SHELTER_BASIN or CANAL and tidewater to maintain the WATER at a desired level as the TIDE_LEVEL changes; a tide lock or guard lock.

Subcode.Label: Levee
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An EMBANKMENT to prevent the overflow of a RIVER; a levee [SOED, "levee", 2.a.1].
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Hydrography Network Lineal Figure Pt, Hydrography Network Areal Figure Pt

Subcode.Label: Dock
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The space between two PIERs; a dock or a slip.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Clearing_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A straight LINE that separates a safe WATERBODY_REGION from a dangerous REGION or that passes clear of a marine navigational danger; a marine clearing line.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Signal_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A station on SHORE from which signals are made to VESSELs; a marine signal station.

Subcode.Label: Navigable_Waterway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERCOURSE that is usable, sometimes after improvements, as a commercial MARINE_ROUTE; a navigable waterway.

Subcode.Label: Shoal
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A MARINE_REGION over which there is a WATER_DEPTH of twenty metres or less, and which is composed of unconsolidated MATERIAL, except CORAL or ROCK; a shoal.

Subcode.Label: Turning_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An enlargement of a WATER_CHANNEL used for turning VESSELs; a turning basin or manoeuvering basin.

Subcode.Label: Wet_Dock
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DOCK in which WATER can be maintained at any level by closing a MARINE_GATE when the WATER is at the desired level; a wet dock.

Subcode.Label: Bombora_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_REGION where WATER_WAVEs form over a submerged offshore SHOAL, sometimes (in very calm weather and/or at high TIDE) nearly swelling but in other conditions breaking heavily and producing a dangerous stretch of broken WATER; a bombora.

Subcode.Label: Estuary
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An arm of a WATERBODY that extends inland to meet the mouth of a RIVER and includes a mixture of fresh and salt WATER; an estuary [AHD, "estuary", 2].

Subcode.Label: Fiord
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A long, narrow, deep INLET of a WATERBODY between TERRAIN with steep TERRAIN_SLOPEs; a fiord [SOED, "fiord"].

Subcode.Label: Hydrography
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY and its adjoining SHOREs; hydrography.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Hydrography Network Lineal, Hydrography Network Areal

Subcode.Label: Hydrologic_Object
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A planetary OBJECT related to WATER; a hydrologic object.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Bay
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY partially enclosed by LAND but with a wide mouth that affords access to the SEA; a marine bay.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Gulf
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large WATERBODY_REGION partially enclosed by LAND, especially a long land-locked portion of a WATERBODY opening through a MARINE_STRAIT; a marine gulf.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Sound
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A long, relatively wide WATERBODY that is larger than a MARINE_STRAIT or a MARINE_CHANNEL and that connects larger WATERBODYs (for example: SEAs and/or OCEANs); a marine sound [AHD, "sound", 3.1.a].

Subcode.Label: Marine_Strait
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A narrow channel joining two WATERBODYs; a marine strait [SOED, "strait", 3].

Subcode.Label: Ocean
Subcode.Concept_Definition: One of the major divisions of an expanse of salt WATER covering a PLANETARY_SURFACE; an ocean.

Subcode.Label: Polynya
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large REGION of OPEN_WATER that is surrounded by floating ICE; a polynya [SOED, "polynya"].

Subcode.Label: Prevailing_Current
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_CURRENT most frequently observed during a given observation period, usually a month, season, or year; a prevailing current.

Subcode.Label: Run_Off
Subcode.Concept_Definition: WATER that is carried off a TRACT by RIVERs after having fallen as RAIN; run-off.

Subcode.Label: Sea
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A salty WATERBODY more or less confined by continuous LAND or chains of ISLANDs and forming a distinct REGION; a sea.

Subcode.Label: Spring
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A natural outflow of WATER from below the LAND; a spring.

Subcode.Label: Underwater_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION under a WATERBODY_SURFACE.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A particular, designated body of WATER forming a physiographic OBJECT [SOED, "waterbody"]. EXAMPLES LAKE, OCEAN, SEA, RIVER.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A delimited, principal division of a WATERBODY; a waterbody basin. EXAMPLE OCEAN_BASIN.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Current
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large WATERBODY_REGION containing a WATER_CURRENT that is relatively homogenous with respect to WATERBODY_TEMPERATURE or PRACTICAL_SALINITY and that differs from that of the adjacent REGIONs; a waterbody current.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of a WATERBODY.

Subcode.Label: Water_Channel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: That part of a WATERBODY, sometimes dredged, that is deep enough for navigation through a WATERBODY_SURFACE_REGION that would otherwise not be navigable; a water channel. It is usually marked by a single or double line of MARINE_AID_TO_NAVIGATIONs.

Subcode.Label: Water_Current
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A CURRENT in a WATERBODY.

Subcode.Label: Watercourse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An artificial or natural channel for the conveyance of WATER; a watercourse.

Subcode.Label: Inlet
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A short, narrow WATERCOURSE connecting a MARINE_BAY or LAGOON with a SEA; an inlet.

Subcode.Label: Hoar_Frost
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A deposit of ICE (hoar crystals) that generally assumes the form of scales, needles, feathers, or fans and that forms on OBJECTs the SURFACEs of which are sufficiently cooled, usually by nocturnal radiation, to bring about deposition of the water vapour contained in the ambient AIR; hoar frost.

Subcode.Label: Ice
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Frozen WATER; ice [SOED, "ice", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Ice_Glaze
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A coating of ICE, generally clear and smooth, formed on exposed OBJECTs by the freezing of a film of supercooled WATER deposited by RAIN, DRIZZLE, or FOG or possibly condensed from supercooled water vapour; ice glaze. ICE_GLAZE is denser, harder, and more transparent than either RIME or HOAR_FROST.

Subcode.Label: Ice_Keel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An irregular, linear, downward extension of ICE formed where two moving masses of ICE collide on a WATERBODY; an ice keel.

Subcode.Label: Rime
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A white or milky and opaque granular deposit of ICE formed by the rapid freezing of supercooled drops of WATER as they impinge upon an exposed OBJECT; rime. It is denser and harder than HOAR_FROST, but lighter, softer, and less transparent than ICE_GLAZE.

Subcode.Label: Snow_Ground_Cover
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The layer formed by SNOW_PRECIPITATION as it accumulates on the LAND; snow ground cover.

Subcode.Label: Cargo
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The goods carried by a VEHICLE; a cargo [SOED, "cargo", 1.a] or load.

Subcode.Label: Drilling_Rig
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE that enables EQUIPMENT (for example: a drill and/or instrumentation) to create a hole or to be deployed in a hole in the TERRAIN; a drilling rig.

Subcode.Label: Industrial_Oven
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An industrial STRUCTURE used for hardening, burning, or heating MATERIALs (for example: grain, meal, clay, or wood); an industrial oven.

Subcode.Label: Market_Place
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A MARKET where goods are offered for sale by several vendors; a market-place [SOED, "market-place", a].

Subcode.Label: Natural_Gas_Rig
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A RIG for the collection of natural gas from a WELL; a natural gas rig.

Subcode.Label: Soda_Evaporator
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A shallow RESERVOIR, normally man-made, used for the natural evaporation of WATER for the collection of soda; soda evaporator.

Subcode.Label: Buried_Electrical_Cable
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An ELECTRICAL_CABLE located underground and/or underwater; a buried electrical cable.

Subcode.Label: Buried_Power_Transmission_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SYSTEM of BURIED_ELECTRICAL_CABLEs, supports, and conduits that transmits electricity over distance; a buried power transmission line.

Subcode.Label: Institutional_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY housing an established organization or foundation, especially one dedicated to education, public service, or culture, that provides for the care of HUMANs who are destitute, disabled, or mentally ill; an institutional facility.

Subcode.Label: Manhole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An APERTURE in a utility service OBJECT (for example: an item of EQUIPMENT, a FLOOR, a ROAD, the LAND, a SEWER and/or other conduit) through which PERSONNEL may pass to gain access to certain COMPONENTs; a manhole [SOED, "manhole"].

Subcode.Label: Manhole_Cover
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A cover, which is often made of cast iron, that is designed both for complete removal and to cover a MANHOLE.

Subcode.Label: Manhole_Riser
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE that elevates a MANHOLE above the surrounding SURFACE; a manhole riser.

Subcode.Label: Pipeline_Terminus
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The apparent end of a PIPELINE located above the TERRAIN where it enters the TERRAIN; a pipeline terminus. This apparent end often occurs at a pumping or industrial FACILITY or where the PIPELINE crosses under a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE.

Subcode.Label: Piping_Complex
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of PIPEs and associated pumps used to transfer slurries, liquids, or gases from one LOCATION to another; a piping complex.

Subcode.Label: Power_Transmission_Line_Terminus
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The terminus of a POWER_TRANSMISSION_LINE at a POWER_PLANT, POWER_SUBSTATION, transformer, or receiving FACILITY.

Subcode.Label: Public_Service_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A station that houses public services and from which operations are directed or services provided.

Subcode.Label: Sewer
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An artificial channel or conduit, usually covered and under the TERRAIN, for carrying off and discharging waste, storm WATER, and/or refuse from BUILDINGs and BUILT_UP_REGIONs; a sewer [SOED, "sewer", 2.a].

Subcode.Label: Sludge_Gate
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A GATE used to regulate the flow of sludge from a SETTLING_POND; a sludge gate.

Subcode.Label: Transmission_Station
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A station that is equipped for radio and/or television transmission.

Subcode.Label: Bridge_Platform
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE that has been sculpted (for example: levelled) to support and/or secure a BRIDGE_PIER; a bridge platform.

Subcode.Label: Bus_Stop
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LOCATION where buses and coaches regularly stop to take on and/or let off passengers; a bus-stop [SOED, "bus-stop"].

Subcode.Label: Causeway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A raised ROAD supported by a solid STRUCTURE and/or raised LAND providing a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE across either a wet TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION or an intertidal TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION; a causeway.

Subcode.Label: Driveway
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A private ROAD alongside, in front of, or leading to a BUILDING (for example: a HOUSE and/or a PARKING_GARAGE); a driveway [SOED, "driveway"].

Subcode.Label: Engineer_Bridge
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A temporary BRIDGE spanning and providing passage over a TERRAIN_OBSTACLE (for example: a WATERBODY and/or a GULLY); an engineer bridge.

Subcode.Label: Land_Transportation_Route
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE located principally on LAND.

Subcode.Label: Level_Crossing
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A CROSSING between a RAILWAYand either a ROAD or another RAILWAY on the same vertical level; a level crossing or on-grade crossing.

Subcode.Label: Log_Crib
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LOG_OBSTACLE that is formed in a cribwork and filled with SOIL and STONEs.

Subcode.Label: Mobile_Bridge_System
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SYSTEM that is transported on a VEHICLE and used to erect semi-permanent BRIDGEs; a mobile bridge system.

Subcode.Label: Overpass
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BRIDGE used to provide clearance to traffic on a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE at a lower elevation; an overpass.

Subcode.Label: Railway_Signal_Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An automated or manned STRUCTURE located adjacent to a RAILWAY that displays control information to passing TRAINs; a railway signal structure.

Subcode.Label: Railway_Track
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A rail or two parallel rails on which a TRAIN, tram, or RAIL_WAGON runs; a railway track.

Subcode.Label: Rock_Drop
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A massive assemblage of MATERIAL, usually in the form of large concrete blocks and/or cylinders, suspended above or beside a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE, ready to be activated as a potential BARRIER; a rock drop.

Subcode.Label: Route_Lane
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A COMPONENT of a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE that is typically designated by painted lines, is used to segregate the flow of GROUND_VEHICLEs according to speed or intended DIRECTION, and has enough WIDTH to pass a single file of GROUND_VEHICLEs; a route lane [SOED, "lane", 2.d].
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Sidewalk
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A paved pedestrian walkway, usually made of concrete, typically located adjacent and parallel to a ROAD; a sidewalk.

Subcode.Label: Tunnel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A passage under the TERRAIN that is open at both ends and usually contains a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE; a tunnel.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Viaduct
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE consisting of a series of arches or TOWERs supporting a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE across a TERRAIN_DEPRESSION; a viaduct.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Weapon_Fighting_Pos_Access_Route
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The concealed access RAMP or LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE leading from the exterior of a WEAPON_FIGHTING_POSITION to the WEAPON_FULL_DEFILADE_POSITION and then to the WEAPON_HULL_DEFILADE_POSITION; a weapon fighting position access route.

Subcode.Label: Bioluminescence
