Subcode.Concept_Definition: The production of light without sensible heat by LIVING_ORGANISMs as a result of chemical reaction either within cells or organs or extracellulary in some form of secretion; bioluminescence.

Subcode.Label: Display_Light
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A specially constructed LIGHT that illuminates DISPLAY_SIGNs or other STRUCTUREs; a display light.

Subcode.Label: Phosphorescent_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A phosphorescent WATERBODY_REGION.

Subcode.Label: Shadow
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of partial darkness produced by an OBJECT intercepting rays of light (for example: the direct rays of the SUN); a shadow.

Subcode.Label: Shore
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The narrow TERRAIN_STRIP in immediate contact with a WATERBODY, including the TRACT between high and low water LINEs; a shore.

Subcode.Label: Alga
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PROTIST capable of photosynthesis; an alga [SOED, "alga"]. EXAMPLES SEAWEED, many unicellular and filamentous LIVING_ORGANISMs.

Subcode.Label: Fungus
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LIVING_ORGANISM of the kingdom Fungi, the members of which lack chlorophyll and grow on and obtain nutriment from organic matter; a fungus [SOED, "fungus"]. EXAMPLES MUSHROOM, toadstool, mould, rust, yeast, fungus constituent of a LICHEN.

Subcode.Label: Lichen
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A composite LIVING_ORGANISM formed by the association of ALGA with FUNGUS and occurring as encrusting or branching friable growths on SURFACEs, to which they give a green, grey, or yellow colour; a lichen [SOED, "lichen"].

Subcode.Label: Living_Organism
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A living thing; a living organism or life-form [SOED, "life-form"].

Subcode.Label: Moneran
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LIVING_ORGANISM of the kingdom Monera, which comprises all prokaryotic single-celled organisms; a moneran [SOED, "monera"]. EXAMPLES Bacterium, cyanophyte.

Subcode.Label: Mushroom
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FUNGUS of phylum Basidiomycota, the members of which have a fleshy, fruiting body, usually rounded or caplike, on a stalk growing from the ground; a mushroom [SOED, "mushroom"].

Subcode.Label: Plankton
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Zooplankton or phytoplankton that is passively floating or drifting in a WATERBODY; plankton [MWCD, "plankton"].

Subcode.Label: Protist
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LIVING_ORGANISM of the kingdom Protista, the members of which are simple organisms that are between, or distinct from, ANIMALs and PLANTs, especially a unicellular eukaryote; a protist [SOED, "protist"]. EXAMPLES Protozoan, single-celled ALGA.

Subcode.Label: Centre_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A real or imaginary LINE indicating and/or marking the cross-sectional centre of an OBJECT along its primary extent; a centre-line.

Subcode.Label: Direction
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A direction in relation to a LOCATION. EXAMPLES Course, bearing.

Subcode.Label: Hazard_Marker
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A MARKER placed near or on a TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION or TERRAIN_SURFACE_OBJECT to identify it as a potential hazard.

Subcode.Label: High_Pressure_Centre
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The LOCATION of the centre of an ATMOSPHERE_REGION of high ATM_PRESSURE.

Subcode.Label: Isopleth
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LINE defined by LOCATIONs for which some chosen quantity has the same value; an isopleth [SOED, "isopleth", 1].

Subcode.Label: Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A curve connecting a SET of two or more LOCATIONs; a line [SOED, "line", n2.III.14.b] or a curve.

Subcode.Label: Location
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A spatial location.

Subcode.Label: Planetary_Pole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Either of the two LOCATIONs where the axis of rotation of a PLANET intersects the PLANETARY_SURFACE; a planetary pole.

Subcode.Label: Railway_Nexus
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A representation of one or more RAILWAYs, especially in a BUILT_UP_REGION; a railway centre-line or railway nexus.

Subcode.Label: Ray_Path
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An imaginary LINE along which energy associated with a LOCATION on a wave front moves; a ray path.

Subcode.Label: Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A usually contiguous subset of the environment that may include TERRAIN, a WATERBODY, the ATMOSPHERE, and/or SPACE; a region.

Subcode.Label: Relative_Displacement_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LINE connecting LOCATIONs having a constant relative vertical offset from the TERRAIN; a relative displacement line.

Subcode.Label: River_Nexus
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A representation of one or more RIVERs; a river centre-line or river nexus.

Subcode.Label: Site
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The LOCATION of an actual or planned NON_EMPTY_SET of STRUCTUREs; a site [AHD, "site", 1].

Subcode.Label: Transportation_Route
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A ROUTE used for transportation.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Variable_Displacement_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LINE connecting LOCATIONs having a varying relative vertical offset from the TERRAIN; a variable displacement line.

Subcode.Label: Wadi_Nexus
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The representation of one or more WADIs; a wadi centre-line or wadi nexus.

Subcode.Label: Abatis
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A defence constructed by placing felled TREEs lengthwise one over the other with their branches towards the enemy's line; an abatis [SOED, "abatis"].

Subcode.Label: Air_Defence_Artillery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Ground based surface to air WEAPONs for engaging AIRCRAFT and MISSILE targets; air defence artillery.

Subcode.Label: Breach
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An APERTURE in an obstacle (for example: a FORTIFICATION, a WALL, and/or a TERRAIN_OBSTACLE), particularly one caused by violence or natural decay; a breach.

Subcode.Label: Breach_Hole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A rough APERTURE for entrance and/or egress of HUMANs, typically about 60 centimetres in diameter; a breach hole.

Subcode.Label: Defensive_Position
Subcode.Concept_Definition: One or more STRUCTUREs constructed for the military defence of a SITE that are resistant to MUNITIONs; a defensive position.

Subcode.Label: Defensive_Position_Defilade
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION affording protection or shielding from hostile ground observation and flat projecting fire; the protection is provided by a TERRAIN_OBSTACLE (for example: a DEFENSIVE_POSITION, a HILL, and/or a PARAPET); a defensive position defilade.

Subcode.Label: Field_Artillery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large-calibre firing WEAPON; a field artillery piece. EXAMPLES Howitzer, cannon.

Subcode.Label: Fighting_Position
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A configuration of LAND and/or STRUCTUREs that is intended to accommodate MILITARY_PERSONNEL, military EQUIPMENT, and/or military GROUND_VEHICLEs; that provides cover and concealment from direct and potentially indirect fire; and that affords effective use of WEAPONs; a fighting position.

Subcode.Label: Individual_Fighting_Position
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FIGHTING_POSITION designed to accommodate an individual soldier and that soldier's EQUIPMENT.

Subcode.Label: Land_Minefield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A MINEFIELD on LAND.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Minefield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A marine MINEFIELD.

Subcode.Label: Minefield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION throughout which EXPLOSIVE_MINEs have been laid; a minefield.

Subcode.Label: Missile
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A destructive projectile that during part or all of its course is self-propelling and directed by remote control or automatically; a missile [SOED, "guided missile"].

Subcode.Label: Mortar
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A muzzle loading cannon for firing shells at low velocities, short ranges, and high trajectories; a mortar [AHD, "mortar", 3.a].

Subcode.Label: Parapet
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An EMBANKMENT, especially one on top of a WALL or RAMPART or in front of a MILITARY_TRENCH, that is built to provide protection from an enemy's observation and fire, to protect EQUIPMENT, to stabilize an adjacent STRUCTURE, or to serve as a TERRAIN_OBSTACLE; a parapet [SOED, "parapet", 1.

Subcode.Label: Prohibited_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION, usually on a MILITARY_INSTALLATION, where entrance or presence of unauthorized PERSONNEL is prohibited, typically due to the presence of unexploded MUNITIONs, EXPLOSIVE_MINEs, or sensitive environmental habitats; a prohibited region.

Subcode.Label: Self_Propelled_Artillery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Self-propelled FIELD_ARTILLERY.

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Crater
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A localized TERRAIN_DEPRESSION created by an explosion and/or the impact of a large or high-velocity projectile upon the TERRAIN; a crater [SOED, "crater", 2].

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Transportation_Abatis
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An ABATIS blocking movement on a LAND_TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE.

Subcode.Label: Towed_Artillery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Towed FIELD_ARTILLERY.

Subcode.Label: Weapon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: EQUIPMENT intended to inflict bodily harm, especially one used in warfare to overcome an enemy and/or repel a hostile attack; a weapon [SOED, "weapon", 1a].

Subcode.Label: Weapon_Fighting_Position
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FIGHTING_POSITION designed to accommodate an individual WEAPON, which may be mounted on a VEHICLE.

Subcode.Label: Weapon_Full_Defilade_Position
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The REGION within a WEAPON_FIGHTING_POSITION in which the entire WEAPON is hidden from enemy view and fire; a weapon full defilade position.

Subcode.Label: Weapon_Hull_Defilade_Position
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The REGION within a WEAPON_FIGHTING_POSITION in which only the fighting COMPONENT of the WEAPON is exposed to enemy fire or view; a weapon hull defilade position.

Subcode.Label: Weapon_System
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WEAPON together with all the EQUIPMENT (for example: detection and control apparatus, a launcher, and/or a delivery VEHICLE) required to make use of it; a weapon system [SOED, "weapon system"].

Subcode.Label: Butte
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A detached, flat-topped HILL or tableland that is smaller than a MESA and rises steeply from a surrounding TERRAIN_PLAIN; a butte.

Subcode.Label: Canyon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A deep GORGE, frequently with a RIVER at its bottom; a canyon [SOED, "canyon", A].

Subcode.Label: Desert_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A dry, often sandy, TRACT of little rainfall, extreme AIR_TEMPERATUREs, and sparse VEGETATION; a desert region [AHD, "desert", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Dry_Lake
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A nearly level TRACT at the bottom of an undrained GEOGRAPHIC_BASIN in a DESERT_REGION, sometimes temporarily covered with WATER; a dry lake.

Subcode.Label: Excavation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An excavated space in the TERRAIN; an excavation [SOED, "excavation", 2], a cavity, or a hollow.

Subcode.Label: Filled_Terrain
Subcode.Concept_Definition: BUILT_UP_TERRAIN that has been brought to a required higher TERRAIN_ELEVATION or levelled through the addition of SOIL, ROCK, and/or other MATERIALs; filled terrain.

Subcode.Label: Flood_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT that submerges during the highest known flood in a TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION or has the potential for being flooded (for example: by the failure of a DAM); a flood basin.

Subcode.Label: Geographic_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION that is drained by a RIVER and its tributaries or that drains into a particular LAKE or SEA; a geographic basin.

Subcode.Label: Glade
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT with few or no TREEs that is surrounded by a TREED_TRACT; a clearing or glade.

Subcode.Label: Isthmus
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_STRIP that is bordered on both sides by WATERBODYs and that connects two larger bodies of LAND; an isthmus.

Subcode.Label: Jungle
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT, especially tropical, overgrown with luxuriant and often almost impenetrable VEGETATION; a jungle [SOED, "jungle", 1].

Subcode.Label: Mesa
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A flat-topped HILL or tableland that is larger than a BUTTE and rises steeply from a surrounding TERRAIN_PLAIN; a mesa.

Subcode.Label: Mountain
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A natural elevation of TERRAIN of an altitude that is impressive or notable relative to adjacent elevations; a mountain.

Subcode.Label: Mountainous_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION, the physiography of which consists predominantly of MOUNTAINs; a mountainous region.

Subcode.Label: Named_Land_Tract
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT of natural scenery, defined by its geographical characteristics and known by its proper name.

Subcode.Label: Permafrost
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A layer of SOIL or BEDROCK at a variable depth beneath the SURFACE of the LAND in which the TEMPERATURE has been below freezing continuously from a few to thousands of years; permafrost.

Subcode.Label: Permanent_Snowfield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A permanent SNOWFIELD.

Subcode.Label: Planetary_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The SURFACE of a PLANET, specifically the SURFACE of the LAND and/or WATERBODYs.

Subcode.Label: Plateau
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An elevated TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION that is comparatively flat-topped and of considerable extent; a plateau.

Subcode.Label: Polar_Cap
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of ICE or other frozen MATERIAL surrounding a PLANETARY_POLE; a polar cap [SOED, "polar cap"].

Subcode.Label: Promontory
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A high point of LAND extending into a WATERBODY; a promontory.

Subcode.Label: Ridge
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Relatively high TERRAIN formed as a long and narrow crest that is surrounded by lower TERRAIN; a ridge.

Subcode.Label: Sand
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A MATERIAL consisting of fine PARTICLEs of ROCKs (mainly siliceous); sand [SOED, "sand", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Sand_Bar
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A bar and/or low RIDGE of SAND along the SHORE of a LAKE, RIVER, or OCEAN that is built-up to the WATERBODY_SURFACE by WATER_WAVEs or WATER_CURRENTs.

Subcode.Label: Snowfield
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT covered by SNOW_GROUND_COVER; a snowfield.

Subcode.Label: Soil
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A MATERIAL composed of fragmented PARTICLEs of ROCK, decomposed PLANTs, WATER, and AIR that typically comprises a thin top layer of the LAND; soil [SOED, "soil", 4].

Subcode.Label: Stone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A piece of ROCK of a small or moderate size; a stone [SOED, "stone", A.1.a] or rock (US).

Subcode.Label: Sugar_Cane
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT of Saccharum officinarum; sugar cane [AHD, "sugar cane"].

Subcode.Label: Terrain
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The SURFACE of the solid portion of a PLANET, which may or may not be covered by WATER; terrain or ground.

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Channel
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An elongated TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION, especially one that is relatively narrow, whose longer sides are TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGIONs of higher TERRAIN_ELEVATION; a terrain channel. EXAMPLES CANYON, GORGE, dry riverbed.

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Fill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of fill that augments a TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION; a terrain fill.

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Plain
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION that is comparatively flat; a terrain plain.

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Strip
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT that is significantly longer in one dimension than the other; a terrain strip [SOED, "strip", 2].

Subcode.Label: Terrain_Surface_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of TERRAIN, especially one distinguished by natural features, climate, fauna or flora; a terrain surface region [SOED, "region", 1].

Subcode.Label: Tract
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of LAND; a tract.

Subcode.Label: Tree_Blowdown
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT on which TREEs have been blown down or otherwise levelled; tree blowdown.

Subcode.Label: Valley_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A low-lying TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION located between HILLs and/or MOUNTAINs and often having a RIVER flowing through it; a valley region.

Subcode.Label: Wadi
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The dry bed of an intermittent RIVER, often with steep sides or located at the bottom of a TERRAIN_CHANNEL; a wadi, a wash, or an arroyo.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Bank
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The raised or sloping bank of LAND adjacent to a LAND_WATER_BOUNDARY; a waterbody bank.

Subcode.Label: Wetland
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION that is inundated or saturated by surface or ground WATER at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances does support, a prevalence of VEGETATION typically adapted for life in conditions of saturated SOIL; a wetland [AHD, "wetland"]. EXAMPLES SWAMP, MARSH, BOG.

Subcode.Label: Boulder_Field
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_SURFACE_REGION characterized by detached masses of ROCK usually having an OUTSIDE_DIAMETER greater than 25 centimetres; a boulder field.

Subcode.Label: Fern
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PTERIDOPHYTE of the order Filicopsida, the members of which reproduce by means of spores borne usually on the underside of the fronds, which are typically pinnately divided; a fern [SOED, "fern"].

Subcode.Label: Log
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An unhewn portion of a felled TREE; a log [SOED, "log", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Plant
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LIVING_ORGANISM of the kingdom Plantae, the members of which typically are fixed to a substrate, able to subsist wholly on inorganic substances, and move chiefly by growth; a plant [SOED, "plant", 2].

Subcode.Label: Pteridophyte
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PLANT of the group Pteridophyta; a pteridophyte [SOED, "pteridophyte"]. EXAMPLES FERN, horsetail, clubmoss.

Subcode.Label: Tree_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A relatively linear arrangement of TREEs; a tree line [SOED, "tree line", b].

Subcode.Label: Vegetation
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The PLANTs in a given REGION; vegetation [AHD, "vegetation", 2].

Subcode.Label: Open_Air_Bath
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An open air bath.

Subcode.Label: Convent
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A RELIGIOUS_COMMUNITY of women; a convent [SOED, "convent", 3].

Subcode.Label: Marabout
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SHRINE marking the burial place of an Islamic holy man; a marabout [SOED, "marabout", 2].

Subcode.Label: Mosque
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An Islamic WORSHIP_PLACE; a mosque or masjid.

Subcode.Label: Pulpit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A raised STRUCTURE consisting of an enclosed platform from which the preacher in a CHURCH or CHAPEL delivers the sermon; a pulpit [SOED, "pulpit", 2.a].

Subcode.Label: Shrine
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WORSHIP_PLACE or place for devotion; a shrine [SOED, "shrine", 6].

Subcode.Label: Stupa
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A round, usually dome-shaped, Buddhist SHRINE topped with a cupola; a stupa [SOED, "stupa"].

Subcode.Label: Synagogue
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WORSHIP_PLACE for Jewish worship and religious instruction; a synagogue.

Subcode.Label: Tabernacle
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A CHURCH that has been specially designated by religious authority; a tabernacle.

Subcode.Label: Amphitheatre
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An oval or circular BUILDING with seats rising in tiers around the central open space, used for entertainment and/or public events; an amphitheatre [SOED, "amphitheatre", 1].

Subcode.Label: Apartment_House
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A multi-residence BUILDING containing rental accommodations for hire on a long-term basis; an apartment house.

Subcode.Label: Barrack
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used to house MILITARY_PERSONNEL, which is typically large, unadorned, and intended for relatively temporary occupancy; a barrack.

Subcode.Label: Camber
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small WATERBODY_SHELTER_BASIN, usually with a narrow STRUCTURE_ENTRANCE, situated inside a HARBOUR; a camber.

Subcode.Label: Community_Recreation_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more COMMUNITY_RECREATION_BUILDINGs.

Subcode.Label: Dwelling
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SHELTER (for example: a BUILDING) used for living quarters; a dwelling.

Subcode.Label: Farm_Storage_Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE, often having a ROOF, located on a FARM and used for sheltering livestock and/or storing agricultural products or EQUIPMENT; a farm storage structure.

Subcode.Label: Hardened_Aircraft_Shelter
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A reinforced SHELTER that is resistant to MUNITIONs and is designed for the protection of AIRCRAFT; a hardened aircraft shelter.

Subcode.Label: Industrial_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used for the manufacture of goods or the processing of MATERIALs; an industrial building.

Subcode.Label: Manufacturing_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more FACTORYs; a manufacturing facility.

Subcode.Label: Monastery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A RELIGIOUS_COMMUNITY of men; a monastery [SOED, "monastery"].

Subcode.Label: Reformatory_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more REFORMATORY_BUILDINGs; a reformatory facility.

Subcode.Label: Religious_Community
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of DWELLINGs, BUILDINGs, and/or other STRUCTUREs that houses a community of HUMANs under religious vows; a religious community. EXAMPLES CONVENT, MONASTERY.

Subcode.Label: Rowhouse
Subcode.Concept_Definition: One of a series of essentially identical residential BUILDINGs situated side by side and sharing a common WALL; a row house.

Subcode.Label: Science_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more SCIENCE_BUILDINGs; a science facility.

Subcode.Label: Shelter
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A STRUCTURE for protecting EQUIPMENT or HUMANs; a shelter.

Subcode.Label: Tent
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A portable SHELTER of canvas, cloth, or similar MATERIAL that is supported by one or more POLEs and stretched and secured by LOAD_CABLEs fastened to pegs driven into the TERRAIN; a tent [SOED, "tent", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Tent_Dwelling
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TENT used as a DWELLING; a tent dwelling.

Subcode.Label: Training_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING used exclusively for training of military, police, fire, and/or rescue PERSONNEL; a training building.

Subcode.Label: Transportation_Building
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A BUILDING intended to facilitate the transportation of HUMANs and/or MATERIALs.

Subcode.Label: Transportation_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more TRANSPORTATION_BUILDINGs.

Subcode.Label: Tunnel_Shelter
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TUNNEL for the purpose of sheltering MATERIALs, EQUIPMENT, and/or HUMANs; a tunnel shelter.

Subcode.Label: Repair_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more REPAIR_BUILDINGs; a repair facility.

Subcode.Label: Electrified_Railway_Pylon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A PYLON and/or POLE used to support a POWER_TRANSMISSION_LINE associated with an electrified RAILWAY.

Subcode.Label: Exterior_Wall
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WALL forming an exterior section of a STRUCTURE.

Subcode.Label: Load_Cable
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A NON_EMPTY_SET of rope, fibre, or heavy gauge steel WIREs formed into one continuous strand and used for support, lifting, hauling, and other load-supporting functions; a cable.

Subcode.Label: Pole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A long, slender, more or less cylindrical piece of MATERIAL (for example: wood or metal) used as a support (for example: to hold up a TENT, for VEGETATION to climb on, for supporting an ELEVATED_ELECTRICAL_CABLE, and/or for holding up scaffolding); a pole [SOED, "pole", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Pylon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A tall STRUCTURE erected as a support; a pylon [SOED, "pylon", 4.a].
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal Figure Pt, Railroad Network Lineal Figure Pt

Subcode.Label: Storage_Pit
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An excavated STORAGE_STRUCTURE that is lined by an impermeable MATERIAL and surrounded with SOIL; a storage pit.

Subcode.Label: Structure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A combination of COMPONENTs that are fabricated and interconnected in accordance with a design; a structure.

Subcode.Label: Structure_Exterior
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The NON_EMPTY_SET of EXTERIOR_WALLs and ROOF (if present) of a STRUCTURE.

Subcode.Label: Structure_Perimeter
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The perimeter of a STRUCTURE.

Subcode.Label: Superstructure
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A substantial STRUCTURE resting on something else; a superstructure [SOED, "superstructure", 1].

Subcode.Label: Wall_Loophole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A small APERTURE in a WALL in a defended STRUCTURE created for military purposes, typically about 20 centimetres in diameter; a wall loophole.

Subcode.Label: Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An outermost, limiting COMPONENT of an OBJECT that is immediately adjacent to another OBJECT (for example: an ATMOSPHERE and/or SPACE); a surface [SOED, "surface", 1.a].

Subcode.Label: Data_Quality_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION with specific data quality characteristics.

Subcode.Label: Depth_Contour_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An ISOPLETH of constant depth at and below a SURFACE_DATUM; a depth contour.

Subcode.Label: Distance_Mark
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A MARKER that indicates the value of distance measured from a starting LOCATION and consists of either a solid visible STRUCTURE or a distinct LOCATION without a special installation; a distance mark.

Subcode.Label: Hydrographic_Survey_Contact
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An UNDERWATER_OBJECT detected during a hydrographic survey; a hydrographic survey contact.

Subcode.Label: Land_Easement
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A deeded PARCEL granting easement for a specific purpose (for example: overhead POWER_TRANSMISSION_LINEs and/or access to a PARKING_GARAGE); a land easement.

Subcode.Label: Map
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A graphic representation of natural and artificial OBJECTs within a REGION; a map.

Subcode.Label: Map_Limits
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The spatial extent of the REGION represented by a MAP; map limits.

Subcode.Label: Sounding_Datum
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The vertical, typically tidal, SURFACE_DATUM to which SOUNDINGs and HYDROGRAPHIC_DRYING_HEIGHTs are referenced; usually taken to correspond to a low water stage of the TIDE; the sounding datum.

Subcode.Label: Surface_Datum
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A DATUM defining a SURFACE from which elevations or depths are measured. EXAMPLES VERTICAL_DATUM, SOUNDING_DATUM.

Subcode.Label: Vertical_Datum
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A datum (see I19111, 4.9) to which gravity-related elevations and heights are referenced; often taken to correspond to MSL; the vertical datum.

Subcode.Label: Cargo_Container
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large reusable CONTAINER that is designed for the efficient handling of CARGO by accommodating smaller cartons and/or cases in a single shipment.

Subcode.Label: Catwalk
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A suspended narrow footway or platform; a catwalk.

Subcode.Label: Cross_Country_Barrier
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A permanent or semi-permanent BARRIER placed across any TERRAIN to prevent GROUND_VEHICLE or pedestrian traffic.

Subcode.Label: Mooring_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A LOAD_CABLE used for mooring; a mooring line.

Subcode.Label: Route_Component
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A COMPONENT of a ROUTE.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Traffic_Separation_Scheme
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A measure for organizing a TRANSPORTATION_ROUTE that separates opposing streams of VESSELs by appropriate means, including the establishment of ROUTE_LANEs; a traffic separation scheme.
Subcode.Recommended_Dataset_Component: Road Network Lineal, Railroad Network Lineal

Subcode.Label: Wire_Obstacle
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_OBSTACLE constructed of WIRE, usually containing barbs or razors; a wire obstacle.

Subcode.Label: Agricultural_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY involved in crop production, the raising of livestock, and/or the storage or transportation of either MATERIALs important to or the results of agricultural production.

Subcode.Label: Aircraft_Landing_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A designated REGION of a PLANETARY_SURFACE where landing by AIRCRAFT is possible; a landing zone.

Subcode.Label: Aircraft_Storage_Tract
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A defined paved or hard-packed TRACT intended for long-term parking and storage of AIRCRAFT.

Subcode.Label: Airstrip
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An AIRFIELD with very limited FACILITYs; an airstrip.

Subcode.Label: Arboretum
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A culturally designated TRACT where rare TREEs are cultivated and displayed; an arboretum [SOED, "arboretum"].

Subcode.Label: Cargo_Container_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY used to store CARGO_CONTAINERs.

Subcode.Label: City
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A concentration of DWELLINGs, COMMERCIAL_BUILDINGs, INDUSTRIAL_BUILDINGs, and other STRUCTUREs where HUMANs have settled that is larger than a TOWN and usually smaller than a BUILT_UP_REGION; a city.

Subcode.Label: Extraction_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY for extracting and/or exploiting natural resources; an extraction facility.

Subcode.Label: Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION that includes MAN_MADE_OBJECTs intended to serve a particular purpose; a facility.

Subcode.Label: Farm
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE, including support STRUCTUREs, used for agricultural or aquacultural production; a farm.

Subcode.Label: Firebreak
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A cleared or ploughed TERRAIN_STRIP that is constructed as a BARRIER against the spread of a forest or prairie fire; a firebreak [SOED, "fire-break"].

Subcode.Label: Grounds
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A large enclosed TRACT surrounding or attached to a BUILDING, most commonly a HOUSE; grounds [SOED, "ground", 13].

Subcode.Label: Heavy_Industrial_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY devoted to the processing of MATERIAL and/or the manufacture of goods (for example: steel, aluminum, glass, or MOTOR_VEHICLEs) that generally require significant EQUIPMENT, MATERIAL, and energy inputs; a heavy industrial facility.

Subcode.Label: Indigenous_Burial_Ground
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A CEMETERY for native peoples, generally without MEMORIAL_MONUMENTs; an indigenous burial ground.

Subcode.Label: Indigenous_Peoples_Reserve
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACTand associated STRUCTUREs set apart specifically for the use of a native people; an indigenous peoples reserve.

Subcode.Label: Land_Fish_Hatchery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FISH_HATCHERY located entirely on LAND.

Subcode.Label: Landfill
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT used for solid waste disposal by burying refuse between layers of SOIL to fill in or reclaim low-lying LAND; a landfill [SOED, "landfill", b].

Subcode.Label: Light_Industrial_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY devoted to the manufacture of goods (for example: electronic DEVICEs and/or computer software) that generally require only limited MATERIAL and energy inputs; a light industrial facility.

Subcode.Label: Marine_Port
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A marine FACILITY, usually located in a HARBOUR, that provides terminal and transfer facilities for loading and discharging CARGO and/or passengers; a marine port.

Subcode.Label: Military_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A military FACILITY.

Subcode.Label: Municipal_Utility_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY devoted to the provision of utility services (for example: electricity, telecommunications, gas, WATER, sewage, trash collection, and/or trash disposal) to the residents of a locally governed REGION or municipality.

Subcode.Label: Museum_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more MUSEUM_BUILDINGs.

Subcode.Label: Nuclear_Weapons_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY used for the construction, assembly, storage, or dismantling of nuclear WEAPONs.

Subcode.Label: Ore_Refinery
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An INDUSTRIAL_WORKS for purifying ores (for example: copper and/or silver) and extracting from them various metal and chemical products; an ore refinery.

Subcode.Label: Petroleum_Tank_Farm
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY devoted to the storage of PETROLEUM through the use of a collection of, generally above ground, STORAGE_TANKs; a petroleum tank farm [SOED, "tank farm"].

Subcode.Label: Prepared_Defensive_Position_Site
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A SITE containing one or more prepared DEFENSIVE_POSITIONs.

Subcode.Label: Prepared_Defensive_Tract
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT containing military STRUCTUREs resistant to MUNITIONs (for example: a bastion, a RAMPART, a FORTIFICATION, a DEFENSIVE_POSITION, an INFANTRY_TRENCH, and/or a BUNKER); a prepared defensive tract.

Subcode.Label: Recreational_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY used for recreation; a recreational facility.

Subcode.Label: Refugee_Compound
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY, which is usually temporary, constructed to house groups of HUMANs fleeing from their communities in search of refuge (for example: from war, political oppression, and/or religious persecution); a refugee compound.

Subcode.Label: Regional_Park
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A significant TRACT set aside for public use that generally has few or no BUILDINGs, is located away from BUILT_UP_REGIONs, and is maintained for recreational and ornamental purposes; a regional park.

Subcode.Label: Reserve
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION set apart by a governmental body, institution, or individual for a special purpose; a reserve or reservation [SOED, "reservation", 7.a].

Subcode.Label: Residential_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of BUILDINGs primarily devoted to housing a population, as well as providing a variety of supporting services (for example: a POST_OFFICE, a grocery store, a dry cleaners, a florist, a RESTAURANT, and/or a small RETAIL_FACILITY); a residential region.

Subcode.Label: Retail_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY that is used for retail (for example: for the sale of goods or commodities in small quantities directly to consumers); a retail facility.

Subcode.Label: Safari_Park
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An ANIMAL_PARK in which wild NON_HUMAN_ANIMALs are allowed to roam free in an environment designed to resemble their natural habitat and are observed by visitors riding through the PARK in MOTOR_VEHICLEs; a safari park.

Subcode.Label: Shanty_Town
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TOWN, or a section of a TOWN, consisting chiefly of shacks; a shanty town.

Subcode.Label: Spaceport
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY for the launch, and sometimes the landing, of SPACECRAFT; a spaceport [SOED, "spaceport"].

Subcode.Label: Temporary_Encampment
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TRACT containing a temporary, usually unsheltered, encampment [SOED, "encampment", 1]. EXAMPLE Bivouac.

Subcode.Label: Town
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A concentration of DWELLINGs, COMMERCIAL_BUILDINGs, INDUSTRIAL_BUILDINGs, and other STRUCTUREs where HUMANs have settled that is larger than a SETTLEMENT and usually smaller than a CITY and/or BUILT_UP_REGION; a town.

Subcode.Label: Vessel_Storage_Anchorage
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A defined WATERBODY_REGION intended for use as a long-term ANCHORAGE and storage for VESSELs; a vessel storage anchorage.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Shelter_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A sheltered WATERBODY available for port operations and connecting with another WATERBODY (for example: an outer MARINE_PORT and/or a SEA) sometimes by means of a HYDROGRAPHIC_LOCK or passage; a waterbody shelter basin.

Subcode.Label: Detention_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY for the confinement of HUMANs in lawful detention who are convicted or accused of crimes; a detention facility.

Subcode.Label: Government_Facility
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A FACILITY including one or more GOVERNMENT_BUILDINGs; a government facility.

Subcode.Label: Abyss
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_FLOOR with DEPTH_OF_WATERBODY_FLOOR greater than 549 metres (approximately 1 800 feet); an abyss.

Subcode.Label: Bathymetric_Province
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_FLOOR_PROVINCE of homogeneous bathymetric characteristics; a bathymetric province.

Subcode.Label: Inland_Water_Bottom
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A bathymetric REGION underlying an INLAND_WATER_SURFACE; an inland water bottom.

Subcode.Label: Ocean_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A TERRAIN_DEPRESSION of an OCEAN_FLOOR approximately equidimensional in plan view and of variable extent; a basin.

Subcode.Label: Ocean_Floor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The WATERBODY_FLOOR of an OCEAN.

Subcode.Label: Seamount
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_FLOOR_PINNACLE rising 1000 metres or more from the WATERBODY_FLOOR of a SEA or OCEAN and of limited extent across its summit; a seamount.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Floor
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The floor of a WATERBODY.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Floor_Canyon
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A deep, step-sided TERRAIN_CHANNEL in a WATERBODY_FLOOR the bottom of which grades continuously downward; a waterbody floor canyon.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Floor_Pinnacle
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A significant configuration of WATERBODY_FLOOR topography generally round in shape as viewed from above and of reduced depth at its centre; a waterbody floor pinnacle.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Floor_Province
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_FLOOR_REGION identifiable by shared physiographic characteristics that are markedly in contrast with those in the adjacent WATERBODY_FLOOR_REGIONs; a waterbody floor province.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Floor_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of a WATERBODY_FLOOR.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Floor_Ridge
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A RIDGE with steep sides and either irregular or smooth topography in a WATERBODY_FLOOR, often separating WATERBODY_BASINs; a ridge.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Floor_Trench
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A significant long, narrow, and characteristically very deep and asymmetrical TERRAIN_CHANNEL in a WATERBODY_FLOOR, with relatively steep sides; a trench.

Subcode.Label: Ice_Sludge
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Spongy whitish lumps of ICE a few centimetres in OUTSIDE_DIAMETER that are floating on the WATERBODY_SURFACE of a shallow SEA; ice sludge.

Subcode.Label: Overfall_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_REGION where short, breaking WATER_WAVEs are formed on the WATERBODY_SURFACE when a strong WATER_CURRENT passes over a SHOAL or other submarine obstruction or meets a contrary WATER_CURRENT or WIND; an overfall region.

Subcode.Label: Plankton_Bloom
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An enormous concentration of PLANKTON in a WATERBODY, caused either by an explosive or a gradual multiplication and usually producing an obvious change in the physical appearance of the WATERBODY_SURFACE_REGION, such as discolouration; a plankton bloom.

Subcode.Label: Pressure_Ice
Subcode.Concept_Definition: ICE located in a SEA, RIVER, or LAKE that has been deformed or altered by the lateral stresses of any combination of WIND, TIDEs, WATER_WAVEs, and SURF; pressure ice.

Subcode.Label: Spring_Tide
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The TIDEs of increased range occurring near the times of the full and new MOON_PHASEs.

Subcode.Label: Surf
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The belt of nearly continuous, breaking WATER_WAVEs along a SHORE or over a submerged bank or SAND_BAR; surf.

Subcode.Label: Tidal_Basin
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_SHELTER_BASIN affected by tidal forces in which WATER can be kept at a desired level by means of a MARINE_GATE; a tidal basin.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Surface
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The SURFACE of a WATERBODY.

Subcode.Label: Iceberg
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A very large mass of ICE floating loose in a WATERBODY after becoming detached from a GLACIER or ICE_SHELF; an iceberg [SOED, "iceberg", 2].

Subcode.Label: Surf_Zone
Subcode.Concept_Definition: The REGION between the outermost limit of SURF and the resulting limit of WATER_WAVE uprush on a SHORE; a surf zone.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Surface_Region
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A REGION of a WATERBODY_SURFACE.

Subcode.Label: Waterbody_Surface_Slick
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A WATERBODY_SURFACE_REGION that is variable in size and markedly different in appearance (for example: in colour and/or oiliness) from adjacent WATERBODY_SURFACE_REGIONs; a slick.

Subcode.Label: Benchmark
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A reference mark on a permanent object indicating elevation relative to an established datum.

Subcode.Label: Boundary_Monument
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A marker identifying the location of a surveyed boundary line.

Subcode.Label: Unmonumented_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A formally recognized survey or reference point which is not represented by a physical boundary monument or benchmark.

Subcode.Label: Baseline_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A location that serves as a point on, and which partially defines a segment of, a national boundary baseline.

Subcode.Label: Control_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An object or mark on the ground of known position, elevation, or both.

Subcode.Label: Distance_Mark
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A mark which indicates the value of distance measured from an origin and consists of either a solid visible structure or a distinct location without special installation.

Subcode.Label: Diagnostic_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A point used to check system accuracy. (Retired; this is one of a set of registration marks on an aerial image provided to align the image with known ground locations).

Subcode.Label: Geodetic_Point
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A physical point on the Earth's surface having a surveyed position (e.g. Trig Points).

Subcode.Label: Magnetic_Disturbance
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A localized anomaly in the Earth's magnetic field.

Subcode.Label: Isogonic_Line
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Lines connecting points of equal magnetic variation.

Subcode.Label: Magnetic_Pole
Subcode.Concept_Definition: Either of the two places on the Earth's surface where the magnetic dip is 90 degrees.

Subcode.Label: Geophysical_Anomaly
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An area where one or more geophysical parameters differ from the surroundings due to inhomogeneities in the underground composition.

Subcode.Label: Network

Subcode.Label: Source_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the source data that was used to define, review and/or update the digital representation of a feature and/or attribute.

Subcode.Label: Restriction_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about restriction(s) and/or security control(s) applicable to dissemination of data regarding the digital representation of the feature or attribute.

Subcode.Label: Identification_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about an identifier that is used to uniquely specify an instance of the entity type in a specified scope.

Subcode.Label: Process_Step_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the processing activity(ies) that were used to define, review and/or update the digital representation of a feature and/or attribute.

Subcode.Label: Geo_Name_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity specifying both a name used to denote a feature and related information establishing the context for, and use of, that name.

Subcode.Label: Note
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting unstructured information about the feature, attribute, or related information modeling entity.

Subcode.Label: Point_Geometry_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting geometric representation information about a feature that is modeled as a spatial point.

Subcode.Label: Curve_Geometry_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting geometric representation information about a feature that is modeled as a spatial curve.

Subcode.Label: Surface_Geometry_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting geometric representation information about a feature that is modeled as a spatial surface.

Subcode.Label: Horiz_Coord_Metadata
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the basis for, and quality of, the horizontal coordinates and/or horizontal dimensional measures of the digital representation of a feature and/or attribute.

Subcode.Label: Vert_Coord_Metadata
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the basis for, and quality of, the vertical coordinates and/or vertical dimensional measures of the digital representation of a feature and/or attribute.

Subcode.Label: Sounding_Metadata
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the basis for, and quality of, coordinates and/or dimensional measures of the digital representation of a feature and/or attribute related to a hydrographic sounding datum.

Subcode.Label: Crop_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the exploitation of vegetal and animal natural resources, including the activities of growing crops, raising animals, harvesting timber, and harvesting other plants, animals or animal products from a farm or their natural habitats.

Subcode.Label: Manufacturing_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the physical or chemical transformation of materials, substances, or components into new products.

Subcode.Label: Geo_Name_Collection
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting the set of geographic name(s) used to denote a feature along with a geographic location suitable for use in a gazetteer.

Subcode.Label: Route_Pavement_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about a route pavement, a durable surface for an area intended to sustain traffic (for example: vehicular traffic or foot traffic).

Subcode.Label: Track_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about a railway track.

Subcode.Label: Wireless_Telecom_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about a wireless telecommunication service (for example: radio broadcast or digital mobile phone service).

Subcode.Label: Aerodrome_Pavement_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about aircraft pavements at aerodromes and heliports.

Subcode.Label: Geopolitical_Entity_Desig
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about designations (for example: standardized names or codes) for a geopolitical entity (for example: a State).

Subcode.Label: Admin_Division_Desig
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about designations (for example: standardized names or codes) for a subordinate administrative division (for example: a (US) state, a (UK) county, a (US) township, a (CA) province, a (FR) arrondissement, a (CH) canton, a (GE) laender and a (FR) commune) of a geopolitical entity (for example: a State).

Subcode.Label: Water_Resource_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information (for example: its permanence, mineral content and potability) about a water resource.

Subcode.Label: Hydro_Vert_Positioning_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the vertical position (for example: the depth from a sounding datum) of a hydrographic object (for example: a pinnacle or a wreck).

Subcode.Label: Feature_G_A_Metadata
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting assurance information about the quality of the digital representation of a Geospatial Intelligence (GEOINT) feature and its properties (attributes and associations).

Subcode.Label: Feature_Att_G_A_Metadata
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting assurance information about the quality of the digital representation of a Geospatial Intelligence (GEOINT) feature attribute.

Subcode.Label: Feature_Entity
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An abstract modeling entity serving as a superclass that collects shared properties (attributes and associations) of feature types.

Subcode.Label: Geometry_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An abstract modeling entity serving as a superclass that collects shared properties (attributes and associations) of modeling entities that specify geometric representation information about a feature.

Subcode.Label: Event_Entity
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An abstract modeling entity serving as a superclass that collects shared properties (attributes and associations) of event types.

Subcode.Label: Dataset
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A resource that is a set of instances of one or more modeling entities selected according to a single rationale (for example: a common production or publication process).

Subcode.Label: Pylon_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information (for example: its shape and material) about a pylon.

Subcode.Label: Series
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A set of related resources (for example: datasets) that share common metadata (for example: theme, source date, resolution, and methodology).

Subcode.Label: Entity
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An abstract modeling entity serving as a superclass that collects shared properties (attributes and associations).

Subcode.Label: Entity_Collection
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A resource that collects instances of one or more modeling entities according to a common rationale (for example: based on a theme or spatial region).

Subcode.Label: Information_Entity
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An abstract modeling entity serving as a superclass that collects shared properties (attributes and associations) of information types.

Subcode.Label: Religious_Info
Subcode.Concept_Definition: A modeling entity collecting information about the religious significance and/or characteristics of features.

Subcode.Label: Anti_Shipping_Activity
Subcode.Concept_Definition: An occurrence of criminal action against a ship.
